<html>
<head>
<TITLE> Hiking picture </TITLE>
</head>
<body>
<IMG src="hike.gif"> 
<p>
This picture of me was taken by my brother in August 1995.  This is the
western side of Mt. Nimbus in Colorado (just west of Rocky Mountain
National Park).  We had just climbed half way up the mountain before 
turning back.  The path we took is visible directly above me, curving to 
the right and disappearing behind a ridge of rock.  We turned back
because we weren't sure the path would be passable near the top of the
mountain, and the loose rock (called scree) that we were climbing was
dangerous.  It was so unstable and loose that at one point we started a
rockslide by pushing a boulder about half the size of the one I'm
standing on in the photo.  Luckily, we were able to scramble to the side
and avoid the falling rocks.
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT08-B26-2</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA041-000766-B021-337</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://starfire.ne.uiuc.edu:80/~kenc/l&d.html 128.174.200.146 19970303034236 text/html 4287
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
Date: Mon, 03 Mar 1997 03:39:39 GMT
