<ul><h1><img align=middle src="Images/4-H.gif">MY 4-H ACTIVITIES</ul></h1><p>

<h2>Pledge</h2><p>

<ul><h3>I pledge my head to clearer thinking,
	<ul>my heart to greater loyalty,
		<ul>my hands to larger service,
			<ul>my health to better living,</ul></ul></ul>
	For my club, my community, 
		<ul><ul>my country, and my world.</h3></ul></ul></ul><p>

<img src="Images/line_rainbow.gif"><p>

Since 1982, I have been involved in 4-H.  In the summer of 1991, I was
inducted into the Virginia 4-H All Stars Chapter.  During my high
school years, I attended the Virginia 4-H Congress which is held at <a
href="http://www.vt.edu">Virginia Tech</a> in <a
href="http://crusher.bev.net/index.html">Blacksburg</a>.  At Congress,
I typically gave a presentation on my latest project.  My topics
ranged from public speaking to BBQ.  From these competitions, I won
the opportunity to compete in the National Turkey and Chicken BBQ in
<a href="http://iglou.com/louisville.html">Louisville</a>, KY, in 1989
and to attend the National Institute for Cooperative Education (NICE
conference) in <a href="http://www.inetdirect.net/">Indianapolis</a>,
IN, in 1990.<p>

I always enjoyed these meetings of 4-Hers from across the nation.  Plus
I got to see exciting things like <a
href="http://iglou.com/lou/sports.html">Churchill Downs</a> and the
Indianapolis Speedway.
</DOC>
