<TITLE>MY UNDERGRADUATE CAREER AT MIT</TITLE>
<p>
<a href="http://web.mit.edu"><H1><img align=middle src="Images/MITnew.smaller.GIF"></a> UNDERGRADUATE YEARS</H1></ul><P>
<P>

One of my friends once commented that every person that I knew at MIT
I had met either through my major, my living group, or my work.  She
was absolutely right!!<P>



<a
href="http://web.mit.edu/afs/athena/activity/a/ans/www/NED.html"><H2><img align=middle src="Images/header2.sm.gif"><strong>  MY MAJOR - NUCLEAR ENGINEERING</strong></H2></a><p>


At MIT, I was a student in the Nuclear Engineering Department.  I
majored in nuclear engineering with a minor in <a
href="http://me.mit.edu/">Mechanical Engineering</a>.  During my time
at MIT, I often attended the nuclear engineering as well as the <a
href="http://web.mit.edu/afs/athena.mit.edu/activity/a/ans/www/ans.html">
American Nuclear Society</a> (of which I am a member) functions.
MIT's ANS is quite active and attracts a large number of the nuclear
engineering students.<P>


<a href="http://web.mit.edu/afs/athena.mit.edu/activity/m/macgregor/j-entry/www/j-entry.html"><H2><strong> MY LIVING GROUP </strong><img align=middle src="Images/Logo.gif"></H2></a><P>


All of my four years, I lived in J-entry
which is the smallest entry in <a
href="http://web.mit.edu/afs/athena.mit.edu/activity/m/macgregor/www/MacGregorHomePage.html">MacGregor</a>.
My fellow entry mates and I participated in a <a href="http://www.mit.edu:8001/afs/athena.mit.edu/user/c/h/chiyung/www/pictures-entry.html">variety of activites </a>.
We played intramural volleyball, we put on a five-minute version of
Hamlet for entry night, we went to see the Nutcracker, we attended a
Boston Celtics game, and we tended to go out to eat quite often.
Every year we also had an entry BBQ with our entry fellow Coach Walter
Alessi.  We always had fun!<P>

<a href="workplaces.html"><H2><img align=middle src="Images/con.gif"> <strong>PLACES WHERE I HAVE WORKED</strong></H2></a><P>

<ul><ul><ul>
<a href="http://www.utnl.gen.u-tokyo.ac.jp"><img align=bottom src="Images/atom2.gif"></a> Nuclear Engineering Research Laboratory <p>
<ul><ul>University of Tokyo<p>
<ul><img align=bottom src="Images/purpleball.gif"><a href="nerl.html"> June, 1995 - August, 1995</a></ul></ul></ul><p>

<a href="http://cmod2.pfc.mit.edu/"><img align=bottom src="Images/pfc2.gif"></a> MIT Plasma Fusion Center<p>
<ul><ul>Cambride, MA<p>
<ul><img align=bottom src="Images/purpleball.gif"><a href="pfc.html"> September, 1994 - May, 1995</a></ul></ul></ul><p>

<a href="http://suntid.bnl.gov:8080/bnl.html"><img align=bottom src="Images/atom2.gif"></a> Brookhaven National Laboratory<p>
<ul><ul>Upton, L.I., NY<p>
<ul><img align=bottom src="Images/purpleball.gif"><a href="bnl.html"> May, 1994 - August, 1994<p>
<img align=bottom src="Images/purpleball.gif"> May, 1993 - August, 1993</a></ul></ul></ul><p>

</ul></ul></ul>



























