<title> Robert B. Turkot, Jr.'s Resume</title>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" 
      LINK="#9F002A" VLINK="#003171" ALINK="#ff0000">
<center>

<h3>ROBERT B. TURKOT, JR.  </h3>
<a href="mailto:bob@starfire.ne.uiuc.edu">bob@starfire.ne.uiuc.edu</a><br>
920 Kara Drive<br>
Champaign, IL  61821<br>
home (217) 359-4616<br>
work (217) 333-6291<br>
fax  (217) 333-2906<br>
</center>
<br>
<dl>JOB OBJECTIVE<br>
<dd><dl>Conduct research on plasma-surface interactions, plasma diagnostics, or other plasma related phenomena in semiconductor technology.
Available Summer 1996.</dl></dl>

<dl>EDUCATION : <a href="http://www.uiuc.edu/">University of Illinois</a> , <a href="http://starfire.ne.uiuc.edu/pmi/pmi.html">Plasma-Material Interaction Group</a>
<dd>B.S. in Nuclear Engineering, May 1990, Undergraduate GPA: 4.7/5.0<br>
<dd>M.S. in Nuclear Engineering, May 1992, Graduate GPA: 4.8/5.0<br>
<dd>Ph.D. in Nuclear Engineering expected Spring 1996<br>
</dl>

<dl>RELEVENT COURSES
<dd><a href="http://www.uiuc.edu/admin_manual/Courses/C_D/ECE344.html">Integrated Circuit Fabrication Lab</a><br>
<dd>Plasma Physics<br>
<dd><a href="http://www.uiuc.edu/admin_manual/Courses/C_D/ECE423.html">Gaseous Electronics & Plasmas</a><br>
<dd><a href="http://www.uiuc.edu/admin_manual/Courses/C_D/ECE342.html">Electronic Circuits Lab</a><br>
<dd><a href="http://www.uiuc.edu/admin_manual/Courses/C_D/ECE340.html">Solid State Electronic Devices</a><br>
<dd>Computer Simulations in Material Science<br>
<dd>Materials Characterization Lab<br>
</dl>

<dl>WORK EXPERIENCE
<br><br>
<dl>UNIVERSITY OF ILLINOIS AT URBANA-CHAMPAIGN - 8/90 to present
<dl>Graduate Student (Advisor:  Dr. David N. Ruzic)
<br>
<dd>Currently designing a Monte-Carlo-based computer code to study plasma-surface interactions at low energies relevent to plasma etching and deposition.  Presently studying plasma-surface interactions at dielectric surfaces using time- and spatially-resolved Langmuir Probe techniques in a D&W etching system.  Completed M.S. thesis entitled "Time- and Space-Resolved RF-Plasma Measurements from a Displacement-Current-Based Electric Probe Diagnostic."
</dl></dl>
<br>
<dl>ARGONNE NATIONAL LABORATORY - 5/92 to 8/92
<dl>Graduate Research Assistant (Advisor: Dr. Jeffery N. Brooks)
<dd>Studied low-energy plasma-surface interactions by coupling a plasma transport code (WBC) and an ion-surface interaction code (VFTRIM).
</dl></dl>
<br>
<dl>INTEL CORPORATION - Portland Technology and Development - 5/90 to 8/90
<dl>Summer Research Engineer - Supervisor: Sohail Ahmed
<dd>Learned the standard etch processes in use.  Designed and performed etch uniformity and endpoint experiments under clean room conditions.  Scanning electron microscope training was completed.
</dl></dl>
<br>
<dl>UNIVERSITY OF ILLINOIS AT URBANA-CHAMPAIGN - 8/89 to 5/90
<dl>Undergraduate Research Assistant (Advisor : Dr. David N. Ruzic)
<dd>Performed measurements of plasma characteristics and energy distributions in a 13.56 MHz radio-frequency, capacitively-coupled, plasma processing reactor.  Studied theoretical film growth from a methane plasma utilizing computer codes.
</dl></dl>
<br>

<dl>UNIVERSITY OF ILLINOIS AT URBANA-CHAMPAIGN - 1/88 to 5/90
<dl>Computer Programmer and Laboratory Supervisor
<dd>Instruction of word processing, data base, and spreadsheet programs.
Designed PC-based graphing programs to handle large data files.
</dl></dl>
<br>
<dl>L & B CONCESSIONS - 5/86 to 8/89 (summers only)
<dl>Location Supervisor
<dd>Responsible for logistics, daily planning, finances, and organization of a mobile food concessions unit in the west Chicago suburbs.
</dl></dl>
<br>

</dl>
PUBLICATIONS
<ul>
<li>"Time-Resolved Electric Probe Measurements of Ar and CH4 Capacitively-Coupled Plasmas"  D.N. Ruzic, S.L. Balog, R.B.Turkot, Jr.  Proceedings of Symposium on Dry Process, 1990.
<br>
<li>"Energy distribution measurements in radio frequency plasma discharges using a cubical analyzer"  Phi Long Nguyen, R.B.Turkot, Jr., and D.N. Ruzic, J.Vac.Sci.Technol.A 9 (3), 1991.
<br>
<li>"Time- and space-resolved radio-frequency plasma electron energy distributions from 
a displacement-current-based electric probe diagnostic"  R.B. Turkot, Jr., and D.N. Ruzic.  J.Appl.Phys. 73 (5) 1993.
<br>
<li>"Impurity Transport under Steady-State Magnetized Plasma Bombardment in PISCES-B Mod"  M.J. Khandagle, Y. Hirooka, R.W. Conn, J.N. Brooks, A. Hassanein, R.B. Turkot, Jr.  J. Nucl. Matl. 207 (1993) 116-122.
<br>
<li>"TPX Divertor Design: Neutral Atom Behavior and Optimization for Pumping"  D.N.
Ruzic, D.R. Juliano, R.B. Turkot, Jr., M.Ulrickson, D. Stotler, D. Hill.  Proceedings of IEEE/NPSS 15th Symposium on Fusion Engineering,Hyannis,MA, October 11-15, 1993.
<br>
<li>"Surface Erosion Issues and Analysis for Dissipative Divertors"  J.N. Brooks, D.N. Ruzic, D.B. Hayden, R.B. Turkot, Jr.  J. Nucl. Matl. 220-222 (1995) 269-273.
</ul>
<br>
ACTIVITIES AND HONORS
<ul>
