<title>
Advanced Light Water Nuclear Reactors
</title>

<body background="yellow_rock.gif">

<img src="nuke1.xbm">

<h1>Advanced Light Water Nuclear Reactors</h1>
<h3>Akira Ijuin</h3>

<hr>

<h3>Introduction</h3>

Nuclear energy is a topic that is almost always surrounded by
controversy.  Some claim nuclear power generation will not solve the
energy problem since <a href="fissile.html">fissile</a> materials
will run out relatively quickly, while others question the safety of
nuclear reactors.  Some will say that nuclear waste will cause serious
problems in the immediate future, and others will say it's dangerous
to move around radioactive materials.

<p>

Yet, we still have nuclear power plants.  Considerable resources have
been directed to develop new technologies, new reactors, and new
safety guidelines, perhaps in the hope that nuclear power will help
solve the energy problem.

<p>

Currently, <a href="light_water.html">light water</a> reactor is
the most popular among the different types of reactors.  Like all
other types of reactors, light water reactors have advantages and
disadvantages.  Below is a list of topics that will examine how light
water reactors work, what their advantages and disadvantages are, and
what problems they face.

<hr>

<h3>Contents:

<ul>

<li><a href="nuclear_plants.html">Nuclear Power Plants</a>
<li><a href="lwr.html">Light Water Reactors</a>
<li><a href="safety.html">Safety Issues Regarding Light Water
     Reactors</a>
<li><a href="future.html">So....</a>

</ul></h3>

<hr>

<a href="nuclear_plants.html"><img src="fwd.gif"
align=right></a>

<br clear="all">

<hr>

<address>
<a href="mailto:ijuin@uiuc.edu">Akira Ijuin</a> / ijuin@uiuc.edu
</address>
</DOC>
