<HTML>
<body>
<title>Reserves</title>
<center><h1>How much is left?</h1>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<img src="images/fig87o.jpg">
<br>
<p>To give an idea on how much oil that is, the US currently uses petrolium 
at a rate of 31.15 Quadrillion BTUs (Quads) per year.  
<br>
<br>
<br>
<img src="images/fig87c.jpg">
<br>
<p>It is apparant that we have only scratched the surface of the coal 
deposits.  However, emissions from burning coal are much higher than 
those of oil or gas.
<br> 
<br>
<br>
<img src="images/fig87n.jpg">
<br>
<p>Natural gas (methane) is a likely candidate for use as 
a fuel in fuel cells.  The US currently uses gas at a rate of 24.18 Quads 
per year.  
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<center><a href="index.html">back<img src="images/left.gif"></a>
<br>
<br>
<a href="mailto:dforsyth@uiuc.edu">dforsyth@uiuc.edu</a>
