<DOCNO>WT08-B26-59</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA041-000766-B022-209</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://starfire.ne.uiuc.edu:80/ne201/96webprojects/dforsyth/pollution.html 128.174.200.146 19970303034513 text/html 1810
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
Date: Mon, 03 Mar 1997 03:42:15 GMT
Server: NCSA/1.5.2
Last-modified: Sun, 27 Oct 1996 22:53:14 GMT
Content-type: text/html
Content-length: 1627
</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<body>
<title>Emissions</title>
<center><h1>Emissions</h1></center>
<br>
<br>
Besides thermal inefficiency, combustion of fossil fuels also contributes 
to the <a href="http://www.eia.doe.gov/neic/press11.html">buildup</a> of 
<a href="http://www.unep.ch/iucc/fs025">greenhouse gasses</a> and <a 
href="http://www.epa.gov/docs/acidrain/overview.html">acid rain</a>.  
Recently, concerns 
have arisen as to the effect these gasses have upon the environment.
<br>
<p>CO2 is a byproduct of all combustion and is thought to trap infra red 
radiation that  would normally escape into space.
<p>SO2 results from the combustion of sulfur, and is mostly released from 
high-sulfur coal.  SO2 reacts with water and sunlight to form sulfuric 
acid, a contributor to acid rain.
<p><a 
href="http://www.physics.iastate.edu/gcp/chem/nitro/nitro_lecture.html">NOx</a> 
is a result of nitrogen reacting with oxygen in the combustion chamber.  
Certain nitrogen oxides remain in the atmosphere for decades util broken 
down by ultraviolet radiation in the lower stratosphere into NO, where it 
participates in ozone depletion.
<br>
<p>Fuel cells have the advantage over traditional combustion in all 
categories of emissions.  CO2 
emissions are impossible to avoid unless pure hydrogen is used as 
fuel, but a fuel cell still emits 50% less CO2 than fossil fuel sources, 
even when a hydrocarbon is used as fuel.  Emissions of SO2 and NOx from a 
fuel cell are effectively zero.
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<center><a href="index.html">Back<img src="images/left.gif"></a></center>
<br>
<br>
<a href="mailto:dforsyth@uiuc.edu">dforsyth@uiuc.edu</a>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT08-B26-60</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA041-000766-B022-228</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://starfire.ne.uiuc.edu:80/ne201/96webprojects/dforsyth/ecpic.html 128.174.200.146 19970303034522 text/html 1033
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
