</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<body>
<title>Utility Power Generation</title>
<center><h1>Utility Power Generation</h1></center>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<p>Currently, more than half of the electricity generated in the US comes 
from coal.  Coal, though abundant and cheap, emits large amounts of 
pollutants.  With present technology, fuel cells are still rather 
expensive.  However, there is currently a 2MW prototype plant operating 
in <a href="http://www.ercc.com/scdp.html">Santa Clara, California</a> 
utilizing <a href="mcfc.htm">Molten Carbonate Fuel Cells</a>.
<hr>
<center><a href="index.html">Home<img src="images/left.gif"></a><a 
href="trans.htm"><img src="images/up.gif">Transportation</a>
<br>
<br>
<a href="mailto:dforsyth@uiuc.edu">dforsyth@uiuc.edu</a>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT08-B26-64</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA041-000766-B022-281</DOCOLDNO>
