</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<body>
<title>AFC</title>
<center><h1>Alkaline Fuel Cells</h1></center>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<p>Alkaline fuel cells (AFC) have been in use for more than 30 years by <a 
href="http://www.nasa.gov/">NASA</a> for generation of power and water.  
AFCs have a high efficiency,on the order of 70%, have high power density, 
and operate at a fairly 
low temperature (~80 C).  The problems with AFCs are cost and 
sensitivity.  Very high platinum loadings are necessary for a high power 
rating.  In addition, AFCs rely on potassium hydroxide for an electrolyte 
which reacts with CO2 to form potassium carbonate.  This requires the 
cell to be fed a stream of pure oxygen, which severely limits its 
terrestrial development.
<br>
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<center><a href="spfc.htm">SPFC<img src="images/up.gif"></a><a 
href="sofc.htm"><img src="images/down.gif">SOFC</a>
<br>
<a href="index.html"><img src="images/left.gif"></a>
<br>
<a href="index.html">Home</a>
</DOC>
