<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Advances in Breeder Reactor Technology</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<center><h1>Advances in Breeder Reactor Technology</h1>
<br>
Lecture-Discussion # 23
<br>
Nuclear Engineering 201
<br>
Professor Ruzic
<P></center>
<h2>Introduction</h2>
<P>
 Just as LWR's can be given passive safety features and new designs,
breeder reactors can too.  Some of the proposed designs for breeders
even surpass the safetly features of LWRs.  Since the coolant
for a breeder does not have to be pressurized, one more potential
accident source is removed.  In an accident where some portion
of the cooling system is broken open, there is no force pushing
the coolant out.  One advanced breeder design even reprocesses
its own wastes right inside the plant.  This lecture-discussion
will explore these possibilities.
<P>
<h2>GE Power Reactor Inherently Safe Modual (PRISM)</h2>
<P><ul>
