<title>ICF Target Chamber</title>
<body background="dots.jpg" text="FFFFFF" link="FFFF00" vlink="FF00FF">
<center><h1>ICF Target Chamber</center></h1>
<p>This is one artist's rendition of what an ICF reactor would look like.
<p><img src="target.gif">
<p>The technology that goes into building and using such a reactor is extensive.  It must incorporate 
more than just reactor components.  The issue of radiation safety must be addressed.  Disposal of wastes, 
though not as harmful as those from fission, must be dealt with.  Plus the reactor itself must incorporate 
the technology from areas such as superconducting magnets, high-speed computing, high-power lasers, 
and high-frequency radio sources.
All of these are essential to the use of ICF as an energy source.
<p>What is the government doing to <a href=ICFgov.html>advance technology</a> in these areas? 
<p><a href=outline.html>Go to the outline</a>.
<hr><br><i><a href="mailto:c-lehner@students.uiuc.edu">feedback</a></i>

	
