<head><title>Photovoltaics</title></head>
<body><center><h1>CONCLUSION</h1></center>
<center><img src="fig30.gif" align=center alt="[fig30]">
<p>The growth and advancement bodes well for the future of 
photovoltaics.  By the turn of the century, markets may grow by as much 
as a order of magnitude, the indusrty will have become stronger and 
healthier, and manufacturers will have incorporated the research advances 
of the 1990's into their designs. The resulting higher efficiences and 
lower cost modules should help spur the market.  There is a vast amount 
of energy that lies within photovoltaics and over time photoeletric 
cells may become one of the most commonly used energy sources.
<p><a href="index.html">INTRODUCTION AND HISTORY</a>
