<head><title>Photovoltaics</title></head>
<body><h1><center>CURRENT TECHNOLOGY</center></h1>
<center><img src="b_house.gif" align=center alt="[b_house]"><br 
clear=all><h3><i>This is a solar powered home</i></h3></center> 
<p><img src="b_room.gif" align=right alt="[b_room]">Today solar generated 
electricity serves people living in the most isolated spots on earth and 
in the center of the biggest cities.  Photovoltaic devices, commonly 
called solar cells or modules, use semiconductor material to directly 
convert sunlight into electricity.  Photovoltaics are used to power 
remote residences, satillites, highway emergency call boxes, hihway 
traffic and information signs, water pumps, street lights, and 
calculators.  U.S. electric utilities also use photovoltaic systems to 
provide electricity to customers.  Whether you are a homeowner, planner, 
architect, or someone who pays electric bills, photovoltaics may already 
be a part of your life in some form or fashion.
<p>PV offers advantages over deisel generators, primary batteries, and 
conventional utility power.  PV cells were originally developed for use 
in space where repair is extremely expensive, if not impossible.  PV 
still powers nearly every satillite circling the earth because it 
operates for long periods of time with virtually no maintenance.  PV 
cells use the energy from sunlight to produce electricity therefore the 
fuel is free.  Wth no moving parts, the cells require little upkeep.  
These low maintenance, cost effective PV systems are ideal for supplying 
power to communication stations on mountain tops, navigational bouys at 
sea, and also for homes far from utility poer lines.  PV systems are 
clean and silent because they burn no fuel and have no moving parts.  
This is especially important where the main altenatives for obtaining 
power and light are from diesel generators and kerosene lanterns.  A PV 
system can be constructed to any sizeand the owner of a PV system can 
enlarge or move it if his/her energy needs change.  For instance,   
homeowners can addd modules every few years as their energy uasage and 
financial resources grow.  Ranchers can use mobile trailer mounted 
pumping systems to water cattle as they are rotated between fields.  
These are the reasons why more and more people all over the world are 
taking part in the usage of PV systems.
<p> <a href="index.html">INTRODUCTION AND HISTORY</a>
<p> <a href="CT.html">CURRENT TECHNOLOGY</a>
<p> <a href="FD.html">FUTURE DEVELOPEMENTS</a>
<p> <a href="C.html">CONCLUSIONS</a>
<p> <center>Send e-mail to <a href="mailto: 
jmbradle@students.uiuc.edu">jmbradle@students.uiuc.edu</a></center>
</DOC>
