<title>What's Been Done About It?</title><p><font size=+3><font 
color="#bb00ff"><b><u>What's 
Been Done About It?</u></b></font></font></p>
<hb><hr>
<p><font size=+1><font 
color="#000000">Three Mile Island was an economic disaster, however, it 
was a springboard for a series of changes regarding nuclear power plant 
safety.  The Kemeny Report examined exactly what happened at TMI and gave 
a detailed examination of the deficiencies in design of the plant.  The 
<a href="http://www.nrc.gov">NRC</a> required changes to be made in 
equipment and procedured in all plants.  Reactor operators are being 
trained more vigorously in order to prepare them for less routine 
<a href="http://www.fema.gov//fema/nuclearf.html">emergency</a> type 
situations, and utilities sponsored groups, such as the 
Institute of Nuclear Power Operations and the Nuclear Safety Analysis 
Center, are aiding the utilities in setting and maintaining good 
operating and training practices.</font></font></p><hb><HR><p><a 
href="mailto:browde@students.uiuc.edu">Shana Browde</a> 
browde@students.uiuc.edu</p>
</DOC>
