<p><a name="35M"><b>35M.</b></a>  Marshall, Eliot.  &quot;The Breeder:  Selling the Unsalable?&quot;  <i>Science</i>, Vol. 220, No. 4598, 13 May 1983, pp. 698-699.
<br>

<p><a name="36M"><b>36M.</b></a>  Menke, John R.  &quot;Why the Dual Purpose Breeder Reactor?&quot;  <i>Bulletin of the Atomic Scientists</i>, Vol. 9, No. 5, June 1953, pp. 162-164.
<br>

<p><a name="37M"><b>37M.</b></a>  Metz, William D.  &quot;The Breeder:  French Prototype Shut Down for Repairs.&quot;  <i>Science</i>, Vol. 195, No. 4282, 11 March 1977, p. 972.
<br>

<p><a name="38M"><b>38M.</b></a>  Metz, William D.  &quot;European Breeders (II):  The Nuclear Parts are Not the Problem.&quot;  <i>Science</i>, Vol. 191, No. 4225, 30 January 1976, pp. 368-372.
<br>

<p><a name="39M"><b>39M.</b></a>  Metz, William D.  &quot;European Breeders (III):  Fuels and Fuel Cycle are Keys to Economy.&quot;  <i>Science</i>, Vol. 191, No. 4227, 13 February 1976, pp. 551-553.
<br>

<p><a name="40M"><b>40M.</b></a>  Oka, Y., Koshizuka, S., Jevremovic, T., and Okano, Y.  &quot;Systems Design of Direct-Cycle Supercritical-Water-Cooled Fast Reactors.&quot;  <i>Nuclear Technology</i>, Vol. 109, No. 1, January 1995, pp. 1-10.
