<head>	
<title> History </Title>
</head>

<body link=#0000FF text=#000000 background="backgrnd/screen.jpg">

<a name="start"></a>

<hr size=3 width=25%>
<h1 align="center">  History  </h1>
<hr size=3 width=25%>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<p>The following sections summarize the &quot;History&quot; of breeder reactor technology.  The past economics regarding the use of breeder reactors to generate electricity, in terms of what was believed about the feasibility of commercial plants and the expectations in this area, are discussed.  In particular, the first fast breeder reactor of significant size ever built in the United States or anywhere for that matter, the Experimental Breeder Reactor I (EBR-I), is highlighted.  Fast breeder reactors as a constituent of nuclear energy programs in the United States, Great Britain, France, and Japan are examined over time.</p> 

<p>
<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="econ1.html">Past Economics of the FBR</a><br><br>

<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="ebr.html">Experimental Breeder Reactor I (EBR-I)</a><br><br>

<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="us.html">United States</a><br><br>

<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="britain.html">Great Britain</a><br><br>

<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="france.html">France</a><br><br>

<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="japan.html">Japan</a><br>

<br>
<br>
<hr size=5>
<br>

<p>
<a href="#start"> <img src="icons/up.gif"> <i> Return to the top of this page.</i></a></p>

<p>
<a href="econ1.html"> <img src="icons/right.gif"> <i> Proceed to &quot;Past Economics of the FBR.&quot;</i></a></p>

<p>
<a href="backgrnd.html"> <img src="icons/left.gif"> <i> Return to the &quot;Background&quot; main page.</i></a></p>

