<head>	
<title> Future Developments </Title>
</head>

<body link=#0000FF text=#000000 background="backgrnd/screen.jpg">

<a name="start"></a>

<hr size=3 width=45%>
<h1 align="center">  Future Developments  </h1>
<hr size=3 width=45%>

<br>
<br>
<br>

<p>Several recent fast breeder reactor projects that had been promising were cut.  Of these, the most notable include the Integral Fast Reactor (IFR) and the Advanced Liquid Metal Reactor (ALMR).  General Electric, in cooperation with Argonne National Laboratory, designed the Power Reactor Innovative Small Module (PRISM), which is a fast reactor that does not breed significant amounts of plutonium-239 in contrast to most other fast breeder reactors.  New proposals such as the Super-Critical-water-cooled Fast Reactor (SCFR) warrant further research as well, but less fast reactor research is being performed than in previous decades.  The current outlook for nuclear power in general and power from fast breeder reactors must be examined carefully.  Often, the current constraints to further investment in nuclear energy directly result from the public's general lack of knowledge about nuclear issues.  Like fast breeder reactors, irrational fears spread by the media can also be self breeding.  Therefore, a brief summary of the general educational needs in the future is pertinent to this discussion.  Finally, the &quot;Future Economics of the FBR&quot; and the positive and negative factors facing further development of fast breeder reactors are analyzed.</p> 

<p>
<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="prosall.html">Prospectus for All Forms of Nuclear Energy</a><br><br>

<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="prosfbr.html">Prospectus for the FBR</a><br><br>

<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="attitude.html">Outlook on Prevailing Attitudes Regarding Nuclear Issues</a><br><br>

<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="educate.html">Improvements in Education</a><br><br>

<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="econ3.html">Future Economics of the FBR</a><br><br>

<img src="icons/gls_ball.gif"><a href="factors.html">Positive and Negative Factors Facing FBR Development</a><br>

<br>
<br>
<hr size=5>
<br>

