<h5><p><b>Figure 31.  World progress in the design, construction, and operation of<br>liquid metal fast breeder reactors (LMFBR) from 1945 up until 1980.  The<br>amount and form of power output are both noted for each reactor.  The<br>basic design is either loop, indicative of the early American models,<br>and pool or pit, the type employed first and foremost by the British and<br>French.  In the schedule column, the light shading refers to the design phase,<br>the intermediate shading denotes the construction phase, and the dark<br>shading indicates the operation phase.</a><a href="refrnc.html#53M"> (53M) </a>
