<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Nuclear Power in the US, from history to present</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#000040" TEXT="#80FFFF" LINK="#80FF80" VLINK="#FF0000"
ALINK="#B0A0B0">
<h4>---Welcome to the wonderful world of nuclear power.  You will notice 
that there aren't that many pictures, if any at all.  Well that is because 
they take too long to load up.  So rather put them on my pages, I 
have provided links to some.  I am sure in the future there will be 
some included on the pages.  Thank you and enjoy.--- </h4> <hr>
<H1>Nuclear Power in the US, from history to present</H1>
Nuclear power has been a highly debated topic since its earliest 
days.  To many people, the word nuclear is associated with death, whether 
through war, meltdown, or <A 
HREF="radiate.html">radiation</a>.  The verge of a nuclear war during 
the Cold War increased opposition of anything nuclear.  That along with 
several other problems, including those of <A 
HREF="http://www.cen.uiuc.edu/~d-chang/nuce201a.html">nuclear wastes</A> 
and radiation, has ultimately kept nuclear power 
advancement to a minimum in the public's 
eyes.  They just don't realize how <A HREF="safety.html">safe</a> it 
really is.<P>  However, many of these problems have been solved through 
technological advances.  But the risk of nuclear power is a controversy 
hard to determine.  The operation of nuclear power plants certainly 
involves risks.  But "almost every aspect of our modern technological 
society--airplane or automobile travel, handling electrical equipment, 
even crossing the street--involves a certain risk.  The important issue 
is whether the benefits are worth the risk." (Marian, p. 125)  The <A 
HREF="future.html">future</A> looks slim for nuclear power, but with the 
amount of fossil fuels decreasing as its cost increases, another relatively 
inexpensive source for power will need to be used.  So what is <A 
HREF="nucpower.html">nuclear power</A>?<P> 
<A HREF="nucpower.html"><IMG SRC="fwd.gif"BORDER=1></IMG>Forward to nuclear 
power.</a><p>
<A HREF="history.html">History</A> <p>
<A HREF="present.html">Nuclear power today.</A> <p>
