<p><font size=+3><font color="#bb00ff"><b><u>What is 
ECCS?</u></b></font></font></p> <hb><hr><p><font size=+1><font 
color="#000000"><b>ECCS</b> stands for <b>E</b>mergency <b>C</b>ore 
<b>C</b>ooling <b>S</b>ystem.  This is emergency water needed for decay 
heat from fission products.  Because the valve warning light was 
defective, the operator believed (and rightly so) that water needed for 
cooling was being lost from the tank, so he took the right innitiative 
and started the ECCS.  Normally, this would have been good, had the valve 
not been opened.  Since the valve <b>was</b> open, however, the ECCS 
simply added to the overflow and caused more flooding.</font></font></p>
<hb><hr><a href="mailto:browde@students.uiuc.edu">Shana 
Browde</a>browde@students.uiuc.edu
