<p><font size=+3><font color="#bb00ff"><b><u>What is 
SCRAM?</u></b></font></font></p>
<hb>
<p><font size=+1><font color="#000000"><b>SCRAM</b> stands for <b>S</b>afety 
<b>C</b>ontrol <b>R</b>od <b>A</b>ctivator 
<b>M</b>echanism.  This is a safety option in which the 
operator can lower all of the control rods into the core of 
the reactor at the same time;  the control rods (ususally 
made of carbon) capture the neutrons;  thus the fission 
process is unable to take place, or is at least 
significantly slowed down.</font></font></p>
<hb><hr><p><a href="mailto:browde@students.uiuc.edu">Shana 
Browde</a>browde@students.uiuc.edu</p>
