<BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#FF3333" VLINK="#FFFFFF" ALINK="#FFFFFF">

<h1><CENTER><I>Electric Cars<BR>What is the range?</I></CENTER></h1>
<p>
<HR size=1>

<TEXTAREA NAME="" ROWS="" COLS="">Most electric vehicles today can only go about 50 to 100 miles before their batteries need to be recharged.  However, most people only drive short distances.  For these people, this range would be sufficient.  For others, there are special batteries that can go longer distances.  The world record if currently 238 miles on one charge.</TEXTAREA>

</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT08-B26-158</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA041-000766-B022-69</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://starfire.ne.uiuc.edu:80/ne201/96webprojects/m_duffy1/env.html 128.174.200.146 19970303034348 text/html 2677
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
