</DOCHDR>
<h3><CENTER>Some of the environmentalist's and conservationist's concerns and
demands</h3></CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<hr>
The groups opposing the exploration and development of the ANWR oil resources
see the coastal plain as a unique and invaluable Arctic ecosystem and
wilderness area.  These groups fear threat development will destroy the plains
wilderness and seriously damage the wildlife which resides there.  These and
numerous other environmental values will be damaged in return for a small
potential (estimates vary, <A HREF ="back.html">see background page</A>) that
will only make a small dent in the United States' domestic oil problem.[7]  
<P>
<hr>
<P>
The following is a list of concerns for the environmental groups [8]:
<P>

<img src = "redball.gif">
 The Federal Wildlife Service (FWS) should have lead for preparing the
Environmental Impact Statement (EIS)
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Exploration should be undertaken in winter rather than summer to lessen
risk of significant impacts
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 The time frame between completion of the Baseline Study (complete by now)
and development of the EIS and  regulations is too short.  The EIS, Baseline
study, and regulations should be written sequentially rather than
simultaneously.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Exploration activities should be monitored by FWS personnel having
authority to make decisions to modify or stop activities that would result in
significant or avoidable impacts
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Seismic information should be made public immediately
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Alternatives to resource development should be considered in the EIS. 
Alternatives should be analyzed and compared on the basis of unavoidable
impacts.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Wilderness review should be undertaken concurrently with Baseline Study.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Adequate archeological surveys should be conducted prior to exploratory
activities.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 No duplicate exploration should be permitted.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Critical environmental areas should be identified and excluded from
exploratory activities.
<P>
</h3>
<h4>
<p><a href=govt.html>Government and Business Concerns</a>
<p><a href=impact.html>Impact</a>
<p><a href=alt.html>Energy Alternatives</a>
