<h3><CENTER>Someof the Concerns of the Oil Industry Representatives</h3>
</Center>
<P>
<P>
<hr>
Pro-development groups view the 125 mile coastal plain as the most promising
remaining domestic source for large scale recoverable oil, and they believe
that exploration of this area can be done without significant harm to the
environment or the ecosystems that exist in this area.  As an example, these
groups use the development and exploration of Alaska's North Slope for oil 
production.  Proponents of oil exploration use this example because the North
Slope, which the forementioned Prudhoe Bay is a part of, has been managed in a
way such that there has been minimal environmental impact. [9]

<P>
<hr>
<P>
The following is a list of concerns among the business representatives [10]:
<P>

<img src = "redball.gif">
 Acquisition of high resolution data and use of appropriate technologies should
 be allowed.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Industry responses to questions in the "Notice of Intent" should be printed in
 the Environmental Impact Statement (EIS).
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Confidentiality of collected data should be protected for 10 years following
 leasing.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Any airborne surveys should precede surface work by one season.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Each applicant should be allowed to do his own exploration, if desired.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 No restriction should be imposed on the number of field crews.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Consideration of exploratory activities should nto be restricted to the winter
 season.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 The low probability of worst-case scenarios should be accurately emphasized.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 No portion of the ANWR coastal plain should be excluded from exploration.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 Some duplication of exploratory work should be permitted if found necessary
 for accurate data interpretation.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 The EIS should address the rationale for choosing the proposed regulations.
<P><img src = "redball.gif">
 The issue of possible drainage disruption on the coastal plain should be
 addressed, along with the potential for permafrost degradation.
</h3>
<h4>
<p><a href=impact.html>Impact</a>
<p><a href=alt.html>Energy Alternatives</a>
