<HTML>
<BODY>
<B>
<TITLE>Future Developments</TITLE>
<BODY BACKGROUND = "http://www.students.uiuc.edu/~ca-patel/backgd/stars.gif" TEXT="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#00DCDC" LINK="#FFFF00">
<hr>
<font size=7><center>Future Developments</center></font>
<HR>
<hr>
<p>
Biomass future as an energy source depends highly on the cost of other energy sources on the current market, like gasoline and coal.  In order to become competitive, there will need to be further reduction in costs of harvesting, collection, drying, and transporting of various crops.  There is also a necessity of improving economic recovery and upgrading of spent gases.
<p>
<br>
<font size=+1>Thermochemical</font><br>
The improvements needed for thermochemical processes are making them energy-efficient, determining the optimal operational conditions to make the desired products, and separational technologies.
<p>
<br>
<font size=+1>Biochemical</font><br>
The improvements needed for biochemical processes are simplifing the processing steps, making useful products from the entire feedstock, reducing processing times, and separational technologies.
<br>
<p>

<font size=4>
<br>
<p>
<dd><a href=concl.html><img src=arrow.gif>Conclusion</a>
