<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Alternative uses for MHTGR
</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win16; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="rain.gif">

<H2><FONT SIZE=+3>Alternative uses for MHTGR</FONT></H2>

<P>
<HR>Currently there are only two alternative uses for the MHTGR, destroying
weapons grade plutonium and supplying fresh water. Considering the need
for fresh water and the destuction of nuclear weapons, these are extremely
important.</P>

<P>The first alternative use is destroying nuclear weapon grade plutonium.
This requires the construction of a particle acclerator at the location
of the MHTGR. This system called Reactor Accelerator Plutonium Destruction
(RAPD) could destory 32 metric tons of plutonium in its forty year cycle
of operation. A picture of this system is listed below:</P>

<P><IMG SRC="rapd1.gif" HEIGHT=512 WIDTH=603> </P>

<P>The other alternative use for MHTGR is supplying fresh water. This could
be extremely useful in areas around the ocean because it is basically a
desalinization process. For this use, a Water Production Plant (WPP) must
be added to the existing Nuclear Island (NI) and Energy Conversion Area
(ECA). After the steam from the NI is used to produce electrical energy,
it's waste heat is sent to the WPP. This hot circulating water is the energy
source for the WPP. About 20% of the salt-water can be desalinized into
fresh water, while the rest is returned to the ocean in the form of concentrated
brine.</P>

<P>The WPP is made up of 8 seawater desalinization trains, and a seawater
intake and discharge system. Each deslainization train has a flash chamber,
16 evaporation/heat recovery effects, and a heat-rejection effect. This
entire system is contained in an epoxy-lined steel vessel that is 512 ft
long and 28 ft in diameter. The seawater intake system is designed to take
in 340,000 gpm of seawater which corresponds to 68,000 gpm of fresh water
produced.  Below is a picture of the WPP's evaporation chamber:</P>

<P><IMG SRC="evap.gif" > 
<HR><A HREF="link3.html"><IMG SRC="back.gif" HEIGHT=40 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=LEFT></A>
<A HREF="link5.html"><IMG SRC="fwd.gif" HEIGHT=40 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=RIGHT></A>
<BR clear="all">

<HR></P>

<ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:npederso@uiuc.edu">Nick Pederson</A> / npederso@uiuc.edu
</ADDRESS>

</BODY>
