<body background="stuccobac.gif">
<hr>
<br>REMOTE USES
<br>
<hr>
<br>
<br><center><img src = "August.gif"></center>

<br>Remote applications are an excellent use for photovoltaic arrays.  It is often more <br>expensive to run electricity than it is to purchase a photovoltaic system.  There are <br>many units available that combine PV cells, battery, and controls into a single system.

<br>
<br><hr>
<br>Battery Charging
<br><center><img src = "charging.gif"></center>
<br>Photovoltaic systems can be used to supply a small current to batteries to keep them <br>from slowly discharging.
<br>
<br><hr>
<br>Cathodic Protection
<br><center><img src = "cathodic.gif"></center>
<br>Photovoltaics can be used to prevent corrosion on bridges, buildings, metal towers, <br>and underground pipelines and storage tanks.  This corrosion occurs when metal is <br>exposed to water and soil.  Cathodic protection stops the corrosion by providing an <br>electrical charge.  
<br>
<br><hr>
<br>Remote Communications
<br><center><img src = "communications.gif"></center>

<br>This is an important use for photovoltaics because of the growing need for <br>communications. Applications include mobile radio systems, telephones, radio <br>communications, emergency call boxes, remote control systems, microwave <br>repeaters, and mobile radio systems.
<br>
<br><hr>
<br>Water Pumping
<br><center><img src = "pumping.gif"></center>
<br>Photovoltaic cells can be used to provide electricity to power pumps for drinking <br>water, irrigation, and water for industrial uses.
<br>
<br><hr>
<br>Remote Monitoring
<br><center><img src = "monitoring.gif"></center>
<br>Monitoring stations can be placed anywhere to provide information like weather <br>conditions, factory emissions, and flow rates.
<br>
<br><hr>
<br>Remote Switching
<br><center><img src = "switching.gif"></center>
<br>This is an important application for such things as operating switches on electric <br>power transmission lines.  A photovoltaic powered switch is much more inexpensive <br>than the transformer necessary to connect the switch to a grid.
<br>
<br><hr>
<br>Cabin
<br><center><img src = "refrigeration.gif"></center>
<br>Photovoltaics can provide the low power needed for such things as lighting and <br>refrigeration in rural installations and vacation cabins.
<br>
<br><hr>
<br>Lighting
<br><center><img src = "lighting.gif"></center>
<br>Photovoltaics can also provide lighting for commercial needs.  Current applications <br>include highway signs, billboards, and parking lots.
<br>
<br><hr>
<br>Warning Signals
<br><center><img src = "signals.gif"></center>
<br>Warning signals such as beacons on smokestacks or transmission towers, navigational <br>beacons, audible emergency signals, highway warning signs, and railroad signals can <br>all use photovoltaics to power them.
<br>
<br><a href ="currentapplications.html"><img src = "homeD.gif"></a>

</body>
</html>

