<br>SATELLITES
<br>
<hr>
<br>
<br><center><img src = "satellite.gif"></center>
<br>Since 1958, photovoltaic cells have powered most U.S. satellites in space.  Scores of <br>new materials and many new cell designs have been explored with the objective of <br>developing long-lasting, reliable, low-cost photovoltaic systems for terrestrial use. <br>Today's modules typically provide more than 20 years of relatively maintenance-free <br>operation.
