<HTML>
<TITLE>BCC PREPUBLICATION ANNOUNCEMENTS</TITLE>

<IMG SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif"><BR>

<H4>WELCOME TO BCC LISTING OF SOON-TO-BE-PUBLISHED TECHNOLOGIES
MARKET REPORTS</H4>
<BODY>
Below you will find a list and summaries of interesting reports that are now being prepared.
Listings include our target publication date. If you are interested in ordering a report or would
like more information, send us an email message or call BCC at 203/853-4266. <P>


</B>
<b><P><HR><P></b>

<hr>

<h2>FOR BIOTECH</h2>





<b><a name = "B-205" href="bcc_order_report.html">B-205 Receptor Agonists and Blockers
</a></b><br>
A great deal of biotechnology involves research on receptor biology and the mechanisms of their
signal transduction, particularly since cloning allows the generation of receptor molecules and
associated substances in sufficient quantities to permit their study in isolation.  At the same time,
there are new approaches to developing therapeutic design based on SAR, combinatorial
chemistry, and high-throughput screening technology.  Chirotechnology adds another dimension
to this field, permitting the stereoselective synthesis of new and improved receptor agonists and
blockers.<br>

This new BCC study includes ion-channel receptors, neuroreceptors, hormone and growth factor
receptors, cytokine receptors, and other receptors.  It discusses the latest research on receptor
biology, agonists and blockers in development, and forecasts worldwide therapeutic drug sales in
these categories.<br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>           Prepublication Price: <b>$3450.00</b><P>



<b><a name = "C-056U" href="bcc_order_report.html">C-056U Commercial Amino Acids
</a></b><br>
Commercial interest in amino acids is a direct result of the increasing awareness of the many functions that these substances perform in humans and animals. As understanding of these functions and properties increases, current usage is likely to expand rapidly, as are the prospects for future innovative applications using amino acids. This updated BCC study examines the current and future usage trends of amino acids in such areas as food/beverages, pharmaceuticals, animal feeds, and flavorants.  New processing technologies are evaluated and discussed.  The market for amino acid usage is segmented by value and volume, and by both amino acid and application area, with projected market figures through 2001.  Detailed company profiles are profiled.
<br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>           Prepublication Price: <b>$2850.00</b><P>

<hr>

<h2>FOR CERAMICS</h2>


<b><a name = "DCD96" href="bcc_order_report.html">DCD96 A Complete Guide
to the U.S. Advanced Ceramics Industry</a></b><br>
The U.S. advanced ceramics industry has gone through some ups and downs but is now poised
for steady growth.  This  BCC report provides an overview of the technologies, the market for
each segment, U.S. industry structure, foreign competition and details of acquisition, mergers and
joint venture between companies.  Over 450 companies are profiled in this report.<br>
Target Date:  <b>December 1996</b>                                Prepublication Price:<b>$2950.00</b><P>



<b><a name = "GB-173R" href="bcc_order_report.html">GB-173R Diamond, Diamond-Like
Carbon & CBN Films & Coated Products </a></b>Markets<br>
Diamond and diamond-like carbon coatings and thin films of cubic boron nitride find several new
applications in tools and wear resistant parts, electronic devices, optics and optoelectronics.  The
BCC study investigates the technological driving forces that have made diamond and
diamond-like carbon films and coating the future growth industry.  The report covers coating
techniques,
new developments, current and merging applications, and market opportunities.  Markets are
estimated for 1995 and the year 2000.  Profiles of all companies involved in this growing industry
are also provided.<br>
Target Date:  <b>December 1996</b>       Prepublication Price:  <b>$2950.00</b><p>


<b><a name = "GB-173T" href="bcc_order_report.html">GB-173T  Diamond, Diamond-like Carbon and CBN Films, and Coated Products: A Technical Analysis Including Emerging Technologies, New Developments, and Patents</a></b><br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>       Prepublication Price: <b>$1500.00</b><br>
<i>Both Studies for $3950.00</i><p>

<P>
<hr>


<h2>FOR CHEMICALS</h2>



<b><a name = "C-069N" href="bcc_order_report.html">C-069N  Chemicals for Cosmetics and
Toiletries</a></b><br>
The ancient impulse to improve one's appearance with cosmetics is getting help from modern
specialty chemicals. While the basic types of cosmetic products have remained largely the same
over
the past four decades, many of the chemicals used as fillers, solvents, and active ingredients have
changed due to recent developments in biochemical processing methods. This BCC report
evaluates
the contribution of specialty chemicals as well as biotechnological methods and products to the
cosmetics industry. The study estimates the present and likely future markets for these
ingredients,
taking into account the economics, consumer preferences, demographic trends, product
properties,
competition, and government regulations.<br>
Target Date: <b> December 1996 </b>
Prepublication Price: <b> $2750.00</b><P>



<hr>

<h2>FOR COMMUNICATIONS AND ELECTRONICS</h2>



<b><a name = "G-049U" href="bcc_order_report.html">G-049U Electronic Mail: Technologies,
Applications, What's Ahead</a></b><br>
Electronic mail has become the "killer application" for networking.  For many people it is the
primary reason to buy computers and install networks.  E-mail services abound, ranging from
corporate e-mail systems to internal mail, from traditional commercial on-line services to new
types of business communications services.  The underlying technology has encouraged a host of
related developments, including group scheduling, electronic forms routing, process automation,
discussion databases, document sharing, and other collaborative applications.  In this dynamic
marketplace, new technologies, applications and suppliers of hardware, software and services
abound, creating a confusing array of options for the user.  This comprehensive BCC report
proposes to conduct an in-depth analysis of major e-mail technologies and applications,
addressing all of the relevant issues concerning e-mail technology today.<br>
Target Date:<b> December 1996</b>                      Prepublication Price: <b>$2750.00</b><P>


<b><a name = "G-193" href="bcc_order_report.html">G-193 The Rush to New Television
Delivery and Reception Optics</a></b><br>
While telecommunications companies struggle with video-on-demand, wireless television, and
fiber optic cable capable of video distribution, cable companies are gearing up to enter the local
telephone business with their new fiber optic networks.  Meanwhile, television set manufacturers
and broadcast television stations are looking to the new HDTV technology, and computer firms
are providing all the capability for desktops to receive and manipulate video.  Video stores seem
content to sit back and watch, while their revenue continues to climb.  BCC's new report sorts
out the players, the technology, and the most likely scenarios for future video distribution.  All
forms of video distribution and products are forecast, along with satellite direct broadcasting of
in-home entertainment.<br>
Target Date:<b>December 1996</b>                      Prepublication Price: <b>$2850.00</b><P>



<b><a name = "G-200" href="bcc_order_report.html">G-200 Global Electronic Warfare Market</a></b><br>
The overwhelming success of U.S. and allied forces during Operations Desert Storm has given the defense community a new appreciation for the importance of electronic warfare.  The end of the Cold War, however, has changed the underlying doctrine by which electronic warfare will be applied in future conflicts.  Evolving technologies such as computer networks and smart weapons are changing the rules of the game.  Threat nations are gaining access to new communications technologies such as GPS, cellular telephones and satellite communications.  This cutting edge BCC study covers the technolgies and the markets by product type and application, as well as the international aspects of this industry.  Major players  are profiled.<br>
Target Date:<b> December 1996</b>                      Prepublication Price: <b>$2950.00</b><P>


<hr>


<h2>ELECTRONIC MATERIALS</h2>

<b><a name = "G-032N" href="bcc_order_report.html">G-032N  Computer Software Market
Development</a></b><br>

The requirement of the software industry has been evolving for the past few years due to
consumer needs that run the gamut from word processing to designing tools and entertaining as
well as educational software.  This BCC report will explore the changes in professional and
networking software, office automation, operating systems, entertainment and educational
software.  Additional topics will be global manufacturing and distribution as well as overall trends;
format trends, the legality of licensing agreements and copyrighting.  Corporate profiles will also
be included.  Market projections are through 2000.<br>
Target date: <b>December 1996</b>               Prepublication Price:<b> $2750.00</b><P>

<b><a name = "G-181" href="bcc_order_report.html">G-181 The New Generation of Analytical
Instruments</a></b><br>
The years of incremental changes in analytical instrument features are leading to the creation of
novel devices.  This BCC report highlights the most significant advances in instrument design. 
Covering spectrometers, chromatographs, and many other types of analytical instruments.  A
market analysis is given in terms of such applications as environmental testing, kinds of research,
along with pharmaceuticals and biotechnology.  The growing sophistication of various networks
that facilitate communications between instruments is also considered.<br>

Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>                                   Prepublication Price:
<b>$3250.00</b><P>


<b><a name = "G-206"<a href="bcc_order_report.html">G-206 The State of Major U.S. Analytical Instruments: Spectrometers, Chromatographs, Microscopes, Others</a></b><br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b> Prepublication Price: <b>$3000.00</b>
<br><p>
<b>**G-181 and G-206 together, $5000.00</b><P>


<b><a name = "GB-162R" <A href="bcc_order_report.html">GB-162R    Advanced
Transportation Control Systems</a></b><br>
New transportation control systems are slated by many to become the most exciting advance in
automotive technology in decades. This comprehensive BCC report explores rapidly advancing
automotive control systems which will provide vastly greater safety, ease of operation, and
comfort for almost all motor vehicles. Applications for these systems include collision avoidance,
night and poor weather vision, "intelligent" cruise control, automatic toll collection, traffic control
and auto guidance systems. The study discusses technologies, applications, companies,
organizations, academic institutions, and government laboratories which are involved in this
research. Report provides detailed market evaluation into the next century.<br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>          Price:  <b>$2850.00</b><P>

<hr>

<h2>FOR ENERGY</h2>


<b><a name="E-074" href="bcc_order_report.html">E-074 World Electrical Power
Activities</a></b><br>

Worldwide electrical power generation is projected to increase by over 20% in the next 10 years. 
This additional
electricity will be supplied by a varied fuel mix, coal-fired, gas-fired, hydroelectric, nuclear,
oil-fired, and others.  This
extensive BCC report, gives analysis on a regional basis, shows where the demand for power will
come from, who will
own and operate the plants producing electricity, and potential investment opportunities.  Also
included are the power
plants under construction, as well as those still in the design or planning stages.<br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>                  Prepublication Price: <b>$2750.00</b><p>

<b><a name="GB-197" href="bcc_order_report.html">GB-197 Large and Advanced Battery Technology & Markets</a></b><br>
This comprehensive BCC report will cover the industry structure and competitive aspects of large and advanced battery systems.  Industry concentration factors, environment and trade practices, purchasing influences and channels of distribution are examined.  Included is a thorough examination of the technology involved in primary and secondary batteries, battery characteristics and competing systems.  Large and advanced battery systems and their markets are examined by type (lead-acid, nickel-cadmium, nickel metal hydride, lithium-ion, aluminum-air, high temperature and redox & flow batteries, among others).  Major players are profiled.
<br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>                  Prepublication Price: <b>$3150.00</b><p>

<hr>

<h2>FOR  FOOD & BEVERAGE</h2>


<b><a name = "GA-091" href="bcc_order_report.html">GA-091 Food Processing in Southeast
Asia</a></b><br>
This BCC report covers the importance and scope of the food processing industry in the most
economically booming region of the world--Southeast Asia.  Products, target markets, pricing,
promoting, presentations, and distribution systems are examined in-depth.  Technologies used,
methods of productions, raw materials, and the major technology equipment are  covered also.
Major players profiled.<br>
Target date: <b>December 1996</b>       Prepublication price: <b>$2850.00</b><P>


<b><a name="GA-092" href="bcc_order_report.html">GA-092 Additives for Soft Drinks: A
World Study</a></b><br>
This comprehensive new BCC report will give a general survey of the soft drinks market with 
market
figures, formulations and trends for the carbonated and non-carbonated segments.  The focus on
the
additives for soft drinks  include grades and specifications, regulatory status, market size and
forecasts for the future, and, for some, technical characteristics.  Profiles of main producers of
additives included.<br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>                   Prepublication Price:
<b>$3000.00</b><P>


<b><a name="GA-074R" href="bcc_order_report.html">GA-074R Nutritionally Beneficial Ingredients & Additives/Processed Foods</a></b><br>
Food and beverage makers have used vitamins and other nutrients as fortifiers for year largely to prevent deficiencies.  The current view is that fortifiers also should be used to provide protective influences against illness.  Another area of research is to reduce health risks by lowering the fat, sugar and salt content of foods.  Thus, consumers now demand products that provide health benefits and prevent diseases, and even various governmental agencies are issuing new recommendations and rulings.  Food and beverage makers want to satisfy demand and look to ingredient suppliers for help.  The report looks at all these possible fortifiers and risk-reducers, and analyzes them in terms of social, manufacturing and regulatory factors that foster or hamper slow or fast growth.  Forecast are make to 2000.
<br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>                   Prepublication Price:
<b>$2850.00</b><P>

<hr>



<h2>FOR HEALTHCARE TECHNOLOGIES & PRODUCTS</h2>

<STRONG><a name="C-056U" href="bcc_order_report.html">C-056U Commercial Amino Acids</a></STRONG><br>

Commercial interest in amino acids is a direct result of the increasing awareness of the many functions that these substances perform in humans and animals.  As understanding of these functions and properties increases, current usage is likely to expand rapidly, as are the prospects for future innovative applications using amino acids.  This updated BCC study examines the current and future usage trends of amino acids in such area as food/beverages, pharmaceuticals, animal feeds, and flavorants.  New processing technologies are evaluated and discussed.  The market for amino acid usage is segmented by value and volume, and by both amino acid and application area, with projected market figures through 2001.  Detailed company profiles are provided.<BR>
Target Date: <STRONG> December 1996	</STRONG>									Prepublication Price: <STRONG>$2850.00</STRONG><p>

<STRONG><a name="B-104" href="bcc_order_report.html">B-104 The New OTC Drug Strategies/Markets</a></STRONG><br>
Many pharmaceutical companies are relying on the strategy of changing drugs from prescription to over-the-counter (OTC) status in order to expand markets and combat financial pressures inherent with the impending loss of patent protection.  This new BCC study provides a comprehensive overview and analysis of company motivations to change the status of drugs, regulatory and environmental issues which influence drug status, domestic and international markets, industry players and dynamics, and the impact of new OTC drugs on distribution channels, with an emphasis on retail channels.  A major focus of this study is drugs that have changed to OTC status, the specific markets for these drugs and the impact that the new drugs have had on the applicable markets.  Potential new entrants to the OTC market are also reviewed. 

<BR>
Target Date: <STRONG>December 1996	</STRONG>									Prepublication Price: <STRONG>$2950.00</STRONG><p>

