<h2>FOR MEMBRANES AND SEPARATIONS</h2>



<b><a name="C-118N" href="bcc_order_report.html">C-118N  Zeolites: Markets &
Opportunities</a></b><br>
Zeolite markets in the U.S.-the largest being waste water treatment, detergent builders and
catalyst production-face
expansion as new applications are developed. Areas of increasing interest range from
environmental cleanup of heavy
metals and radioactive contamination to the high-tech area of catalysis in petrochemical and
refining processes. This
updated BCC technical/marketing report investigates manufacturers, markets and new technology
with estimates of
present market size and forecasts of likely growth.<br>

Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>              Prepublication Price: <b>$2750.00</b><p>



<b><a name = "C-180" href="bcc_order_report.html">C-180     Microporous Sorbent
Materials</a></b><br>
Demand for microporous sorbent materials is rising steadily as a result of regulations designed to
provide cleaner air and water and to prevent atmospheric ozone depletion. This unique BCC
study examines this rapidly accelerating marketplace, including molecular sieves, zeolites,
activated aluminas and carbons, calcium oxide (lime), and sodium bicarbonate, to name a few.
Both absorbents and higher-value specialty adsorbents are discussed. New regulations affecting
the microporous marketplace are detailed. Companies active in the microporous materials industry
are profiled. Detailed market projections are provided by value and volume.<br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>                                    Prepublication Price:
<b>$2650.00</b><P>


