The combination of an aging population, advances in polymer research and compounding, and increased use of disposables will drive growth of  medical plastics beyond the GDP through the end of the decade.  This BCC report will present an analysis of current and projected plastics usage for both disposable and non-disposable medical devices.  Competitive resin scenarios are highlighted along with product lines, and marketing positions of major suppliers of medical plastics.  Other critical issues covered include legislation, the environment, FDA's future role and significance of healthcare providers.
