<h2>FOR WASTE TREATMENT</H2>

<b><a name = "E-079" href="bcc_order_report.html">E-079 Composition of Municipal Solid Waste</a></b><br>
With such interest in the proper disposal of solid waste, environmentalists have put the pressure on the government to regulate and implement procedures by which the waste industry continues to diligently adhere.  This BCC study examines the historical overview of municipal solid waste procedures such as recycling, landfill, and source reduction, all of which are familiar concerns to the public.  The study assesses management methods of successfully solving the problem as well as the various legislative issues surrounding this controversial topic.  BCC looks at technology, market value of vitrified products, energy prices, community concerns and industry structure.  This report provides details which enable those interested to understand the advances and obstacles attached to municipal solid waste.<br>
Target Date: <b>December 1996</b>										Prepublication Price: <b>$2950.00</b><p>

