<b><A NAME = "C-053U" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-053U Biosensors and Chemical Biosensors</b></A><BR>
Biosensor technology can do what no other sensing technology can - determine the presence of a compound with exceptional specificity, accuracy, and rapidity, at low cost and with less sample preparation than other analytical techniques. These capabilities are opening up new and exciting market opportunities. This comprehensive BCC report assesses the current and potential markets for biosensors in the medical, clinical, industrial, food, pharmaceutical, consumer, agricultural, environmental, and defense industries. Marketing strategies, product attributes, types needed, cost models, and comparison of devices by substance measured are discussed. Projected improvements, evaluation of performance characteristics and an assessment of selected products are presented. The study profiles the technological and industry changes that have taken place in the past 5 years, with projections for the likely introduction of new products and the emergence of new markets. <br>
Published <b>May 1994</b>        227 pages            
Price:  <b>$2850.00</b>
<a href="C053U.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "C-056N" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-056N  Amino Acids: Products & Technologies</b></A><BR>
Commercial interest in amino acids is a direct result of increasing awareness of the many functions that these substances perform in humans and animals.  As understanding of these functions and properties increases, current usage is likely to expand rapidly, as are the prospects for future innovative applications using amino acids.  This comprehensive BCC study examines the current and future usage trends of amino acids in such areas as food/beverages, pharmaceuticals, animal feeds, and flavorants.  New processing technologies are evaluated and discussed.  The market for amino acid usage is segmented by value and volume by both amino acid and application area through 1998. Detailed company profiles are provided. <br>
Published <b>September 1994</b>  146 pages   
Price: <b>$2450.00</b>
