<H4>WELCOME TO BCC CERAMICS MARKET REPORTS</H4>
<BODY>
Below you will find a list and summaries of all the reports in our catalog. If you have any questions about our report, or are interested in ordering a report, click on the title.<P>
<B>
<a href="#GB-044">New Industrial Diamond and CBN Technology and Markets</a><br>
<a href="#GB-058N">U.S. Advanced Ceramics Industry: Markets, Players and New Developments</a><br>
<a href="#GB-094R">Advanced Glasses & Glass Ceramics-Materials, Processing, New Developments, Applications and Markets</a><br>
<a href="#GB-102R">Advanced Ceramic Powders and Ceramic Nano-Sized Powders</a><br>
<a href="#GB-110R">Ceramic Matrix Composites</a><br>
<a href="#GB-114R">Chemically Derived Ceramics and Glasses Featuring Sol-Gel Processing</a><br>
<a href="#GB-121R">Electronic Ceramics: An Industry and Market Analysis</a><br>
<a href="#GB-152">Wear-Resistant Ceramic Parts</a><br>
<a href="#GB-153">Technology Transfer Report: Who's Doing What With What</a><br>
<a href="#GB-165A">High-Performance Carbon/Graphite Fibers: Highlighting New Industrial Applications</a><br>
<a href="#GB-173">Diamond, Diamond-Like Carbon & CBN Films & Coated Products</a></B><br>
<p><hr><P>
<b><A NAME = "GB-044" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-044 New Industrial Diamond and CBN Technology and Markets</b></a><BR>
The hardest material known, industrial diamond, has revolutionized industrial operations such as grinding, cutting, drilling and finishing with improved productivity and quality. Diamond and diamond-like carbon coatings and materials such as cubic boron nitride find several new applications in tools, electronic devices, optics and optoelectronics. This BCC study investigates the technological driving forces that have made industrial diamonds, CBN and diamond-like materials and films a growth industry. The report covers diamond and CBN abrasives and abrasive products; diamond devices used for electronic and optical applications; diamond and CBN polycrystalline blanks and products; diamond, CBN and diamond-like films and coatings including their devices; processing technologies; new developments; current and emerging applications; and market opportunities. Markets are estimated for 1990, 1991 and 1996. Foreign competition in each category of  materials is also evaluated. Also included are profiles of 300 U.S. companies involved in diamond, CBN and their products. <br>
Published <b>November 1991</b> 424 pages        
Price:  <b>$2950.00</b>
<a href="GB044.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-058N" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-058N U.S. Advanced Ceramics Industry: Markets, Players and New Developments</b></a><BR>
The study presents industry and market analysis for advanced structural ceramics, ceramic matrix composites, electronic ceramics, ceramic powders and ceramic coatings for high performance applications. Markets in each category are examined according to type of materials and application. New developments and recent patents in each category are provided. Detailed profiles are given for more than 300 U.S companies and institutions involved in advanced ceramics as producers, suppliers and users of advanced ceramic powders; producers and users of advanced ceramic components; processors and users of ceramic thermal spray coatings; and research institutions. Each entry examines current involvement and projects future directions. This study is a must for those involved in advanced ceramics. <br>
Published <b>May 1993</b> 321 pages  
Price:  <b>$2250.00</b>
<a href="GB058N.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-094R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-094R Advanced Glasses & Glass Ceramics-Materials, Processing, New Developments, Applications and Markets</b></a><BR>
Advanced and specialty glasses and glass-ceramics constitute  a new generation of materials which are being used for high technology applications including telecommunications, electronics, computers, aerospace, medicine/dentistry, and advanced optical materials. Applications include optical fibers, electro-optic devices, high performance reinforcing fibers, electronic displays and components, gas turbine engine components, biocompatible prosthetic devices, and aerospace structural components.  The new BCC report analyzes the technologies, materials (fused silica, chalcongenides, fluorides, phosphates, borosilicates, vandates), new developments, applications, competitions and markets.  Detailed patent analyses have been conducted for each product line.  Profiles are provided for the U.S. companies involved as producers of glass fibers, composites and components, and users.  Foreign competition is also discussed in each product area. <br>
Published <b>May 1996</b>  
Price:  <b>$2750.00</b>
<a href="GB094R.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-102R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-102R  Advanced Ceramic Powders and Ceramic Nano-Sized Powders</b></a><BR>
The manufacture of high performance components using powder technology is one of the fundamental aspects of material processing.  And recently, nanophase technology has generated considerable attention.  This comprehensive and timely BCC study evaluates the technology for reproducible quality powders needed to fabricate reliable ceramic components.  The emergence of various synthesis techniques for powder manufacture, including nanophase technology, is reviewed in detail.  New R&D efforts, current sales and market potential are assessed.  Companies active in this emerging marketplace are profiled. <br>
Published <b>December 1994</b>             402 pages             
Price: <b>$2850.00</b>
<a href="GB102R.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-110R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-110R  Ceramic Matrix Composites</b></a><BR>
Proper tailoring of composite microstructures can result in substantial mechanical property improvements. These composites are currently used for cutting-tool inserts, wear-resistant and aerospace applications; however, potential applications include engine components, hypersonic radomes, and high-temperature applications. BCC report provides an in-depth analysis of the technological advancements in ceramic composite materials and their processing, new applications, economics and competitive environment with other materials, current  markets and trends, foreign competition and the players. Forecasts and profiles of all players are presented. <br>
Published <b>October 1990</b> 266 pages 
Price:  <b>$2850.00</b>
<a href="GB110R.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-114R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-114R  Chemically Derived Ceramics and Glasses Featuring Sol-Gel Processing</b></a><BR>
Potential new applications in advanced ceramics have revived interest in an old technology: sol-gel processing. This unique BCC study examines the changing markets and technologies which make sol-gel processing a potential area of significant market growth. New applications examined include precursors which cannot be used with conventional glass making techniques, as well as the traditional glass and ceramic precursors. Applications covered include high-performance coatings and fibers, optical fibers, coatings and monoliths, superconducting coatings, and microelectronic devices such as computer chips and switches. Market projections are provided by industry segment by volume and value.  Active companies in sol-gel processing are profiled in detail. <br>
Published <b>May 1995</b>  174 pages     Price: <b>$2750.00</b>
<a href="GB114R.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-121R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-121R  Electronic Ceramics: An Industry and Market Analysis</b></a><BR>
The use of ceramics in electronic components is growing rapidly as a result of their superior physical properties and new technology developments. This comprehensive BCC report examines markets and material technologies for ceramics used in insulators, substrates and packages, capacitors, resistors, semiconductors, piezoelectric devices, and superconductors. In each case, market factors, segmentation and trends are discussed, along with a full review of technology developments. Competitive positions, corporate rankings, import/export activities, foreign developments, and government procurement activities and directives are assessed. The effects of new materials on mature industries are carefully considered in relation to prospects for continued growth and investment opportunities.  Market projections are provided for the next five years. <br>
Published <b>May 1995</b>  341 pages  Price: <b>$2850.00</b>
<a href="GB121R.html"> <I>Show contents</i></a><p> 


<b><A NAME = "GB-152" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-152  Wear-Resistant Ceramic Parts</b></a><BR>
Following a long gestation period, advanced structural ceramics are now a reality.  Among the advanced structural ceramics areas, ceramic components for wear parts constitute the largest market segment.  Applications include: bearings, mechanical seals, grinding media, ball mill liners, metal processing dies, thread guides and pulleys, sandblast nozzles, etc.  The components are produced using monolithic ceramics, ceramic matrix composites or ceramic coatings.  This comprehensive BCC report analyzes the technology, materials, applications and markets for 1991, 1996 and 2000.  All companies involved as suppliers of materials, producers of components, and users are profiled.  Foreign competition is also discussed in each product area. <br>
Published <b>April 1992</b> 261 pages        
Price:  <b>$2750.00</b>
<a href="GB152.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-153" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-153  Technology Transfer Report: Who's Doing What With What</b></a><BR>
Technology transfer offers companies a way to receive more value for their research dollars, but the process is quite complicated and confusing.  It has received increasing attention and emphasis in recent years as U.S. industrial competitiveness has eroded and as the troubled economy causes the massive federal R&D expenditures to be scrutinized for possible cuts.  As defense budgets decline with the end of the Cold War, it has become even more important for the Department of Defense to demonstrate that its programs can also be applied to peace time applications.  Presently, the purpose of the many federal tech transfer programs is to affect better utilization of federally funded research and development resources. This BCC report is a comprehensive analysis of the maze of technology transfer, and of the resources and contracts that have recently been established. <br>
Published <b>August 1992</b> 304 pages 
Price: <b>$1250.00</b>
<a href="GB153.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-165A" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-165A High-Performance Carbon/Graphite Fibers: Highlighting New Industrial Applications</b></a><BR>
Carbon fiber has been used as a fibrous reinforcement for composite materials for the last twenty five years. While defense cuts and declining aerospace demand have reduced carbon fiber consumption, new uses such as sports equipment and industrial applications are accelerating demand. This new BCC report analyzes new developments in carbon fiber technologies and products, new applications, and worldwide competition and markets. Detailed profiles for market participants are provides in addition to extensive market projections by volume and value. <br>
Published <b>January 1994</b> 161 pages  
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<a href="GB165A.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-173" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-173 Diamond, Diamond-Like Carbon & CBN Films & Coated Products</b></a><BR>
Diamond and diamond-like carbon coatings and thin films of cubic boron nitride find several new applications in tools and wear resistant parts, electronic devices, optics and optoelectronics. The new BCC study investigates the technological driving forces that have made diamond and diamond-like carbon films and coatings the future growth industry. The report covers coating techniques, new developments, current and merging applications, and market opportunities. Markets are estimated for 1993 and the year 2000. Profiles of all companies involved in this growing industry are also provided. <br> 
Published <b>July 1994</b> 322 pages 
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<a href="GB173.html"><I> Show contents</i></a><p>
