<b><A NAME = "C-002U" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-002U  Specialty Water Treatment Chemicals</b></a><BR>
Specialty WTC represents an increasingly critical industry with three major markets:  potable water, process water and wastewater. The next ten years will see a switch from lower-performance, lower-priced commodity WTC to higher-performance, higher-priced specialty WTC. At the same time, related retail market sectors will grow at better than commodity material growth rates. This BCC report is a definitive market study and technical summary for manufacturers, chemical processors, engineers, importers, suppliers and users who work with water treatment chemicals.   Projections are provided  for materials and markets through 2000. <br>  
Published: <b>November 1995</b>  
Price:  <b>$2750.00</b>
<A HREF="C002U.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<b><A NAME = "C-004X" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-004X  Flame-Retardant Chemicals</b></a><BR>
This BCC report makes a quantitative and qualitative analysis of the market for flame-retardant and smoke suppressant chemicals in the U.S. Among the market sectors examined are plastics, wood/paper, coatings/paints, and textiles. Consumption and demand for aluminum trihydrate, antimony oxide, bromine, chlorine, phosphorus, and other chemicals are tabulated by volume and value for each end-use market, with predictions for the 1992-1997 time period. The study describes characteristics, properties, efficiency, cost, product developments, market shares, and producers involved. Includes directory of major suppliers. <br>
Published <b>August 1993</b> 227 pages 
Price:  <b>$2450.00</b>
<A HREF="C004X.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


