<b><A NAME = "C-012N" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-012N  Water Soluble Polymers</b></a><BR>
Natural, synthetic, and semi-synthetic WSPs are vying for market position in an expanding market. Developments in enhanced oil recovery, processed foods, waste-water flocculents, cleaning formulations, pulp and paper sizings, and water-based inks have the potential for creating new WSP markets. BCC report forecasts growth by type of WSP and by application, examines important technological developments, analyzes important industry activity, and points to specific growth opportunities. This document is a complete  market assessment, highlighting the big winners, polyacrylates and polyacrylamides; the big losers, gum arabic and non-food casein; the high growth market sector, oil recovery; annd the slowest growing market sector, paints and coatings. <br>
Published  <b>July 1991</b> 212 Pages 
Price:  <b>$2250.00</b>
