<b><A NAME = "C-020AR" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-020AR   Corrosion Inhibitors</b></a><BR>
This comprehensive BCC technical/economic report evaluates the U.S. markets for corrosion inhibitor chemicals on both a corrosion inhibitor-consuming and a corrosion inhibitor-manufacturing basis. Among the consuming sectors discussed are: potable water markets, boiler markets, cooling tower markets, heat exchanger markets, various oilfield-related markets, refining, and others. Corrosion inhibitor chemical manufacturing market sectors include:  chromium, phosphorus, sulfates, silicates, molybdates, nitrates, and others. Ten-year market predictions for both consumption and dollar value are provided. Industry structure, historic price trends, R&D, environmental influences, competition with other corrosion prevention technology, and company profiles are included. <br>
Published <b>January 1993</b>  179 pages 
Price:  <b>$2650.00</b>
