<b><A NAME = "C-020BR" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-020BR   Antioxidants:  Markets, Materials, Trends</b></a><BR>
Antioxidants are compounds which reduce the rate of oxidation in auto-oxidizable organic materials, thus preventing their deterioration. Antioxidants find applications in plastics, rubber and elastomers, food, functional fluids, agricultural feeds, and cosmetics. This BCC report describes the various classes of antioxidants available, their applications, and any restrictions in their use. The present antioxidant market is evaluated and projections for the future provided. Included with this evaluation is a comprehensive analysis of the trends in those industries in which antioxidants are employed. Industry structure and company profiles are provided. <br>
Published <b>November 1991</b> 137 pages         
Price: <b>$2150.00</b>
<A HREF="C020BR.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<b><A NAME = "C-069R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-069R  Chemicals for Cosmetics and Toiletries</b></a><BR>
The ancient impulse to improve one's appearance with cosmetics is getting help from modern specialty chemicals. While the basic types of cosmetic products have remained largely the same over the past four decades, many of the chemicals used as fillers, solvents, and active ingredients have changed due to recent developments in biochemical processing methods. This BCC report evaluates the contribution of specialty chemicals as well as biotechnological methods and products to the cosmetics industry. The study estimates the present and likely future markets for these ingredients, taking into account the economics, consumer preferences, demographic trends, product properties, competition, and government regulations. <br>
Published <b>August 1993</b> 277 pages 
Price:  <b>$2450.00</b>
<A HREF="C069R.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>



<b><A NAME = "C-082N" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-082N  Biopesticides and Alternative Agriculture</b></a><BR>
This BCC technical-market study is an in-depth analysis tracing and forecasting the significant changes in the pesticide and agricultural chemicals business, and documenting the emerging trend toward integrated and low-input agriculture and the various new technologies involved in this approach. The study presents a qualitative and quantitative account of the U.S. market for biopesticides by specific market sectors such as pyrethroids, pheromones, bacteria, fungi and viruses. In each case an assessment is made of the technologies, how they work, applications, market size and potential, field studies and manufacturers. Market discussions are presented within the context of the total value of the U.S. pesticide market and the crops involved. The report gives a thorough account of the various consumer, government and legislative activities that have and will continue to lead to bans on the use of "hard" pesticides and the present and potential impact of these changes on the manufacturers, suppliers and users. <br>
Published <b>August 1993</b> 148 pages 
Price: <b>$2450.00</b>
<A HREF="C082N.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<b><A NAME = "C-119" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-119  The Agricultural Chemicals Industry</b></a><BR>
BCC report analyzes the changing demand for agricultural chemicals in the U.S., driven by new technologies, LISA, public concern, and government regulations. Five-year forecasts are presented for fertilizers, herbicides, insecticides, and fungicides by the major agricultural sections: field crops, fruits and vegetables, and forage crops. A quantitative description of the agricultural chemical industry is presented.  Among the issues addressed are trends in domestic consumption, production and pricing, government price support programs, major worldwide shifts, industry structure, potential opportunities, and biotechnology. <br>
Published <b>April 1991</b> 186 pages 
Price:  <b>$1950.00</b>
