<b><A NAME = "C-125" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-125  Mold Release Agents</b></a><BR>
This BCC report examines the present and future markets for mold release compounds in the U.S. Particular attention is given to developments in the relatively new semi-permanents, although parting agents (mica, silica, talc), calcium stearate, zinc stearate, soaps, waxes, silicones, polyglycols, and other topical coatings are also analyzed in detail. Techno-economic factors in each of the end-use markets are also analyzed. Trends in mode of delivery are examined in light of CFC regulations. The competitive positions of main players in the market and the strategic options they face are also discussed, as are such competitive factors as marketing, technical servicing, distribution and operations. <br>
Published <b>June 1990</b> 133 pages 
Price:  <b>$2450.00</b>
