<b><A NAME = "C-132A" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-132A  Sorbents and Other Materials for Non-Spill Applications</b></a><BR>
This BCC analysis examines the present and potential technologies and markets for sorbent materials used in process stream treatment, catalysis, water-scavenging in anhydrous reagents and chemicals, ion exchange, and chromatography.  Materials include activated carbon, activated alumina, silica gel, zeolites, molecular sieves, ion exchange resins, microsponges, and others.  Materials and processes are each discussed in terms of the products, applications, and markets within the consumer, industrial and research sectors with estimates and forecasts for the next five-year period.  The comprehensive report describes the industry structure and identifies its players, analyzes the economics and pricing criteria, lists patents and R&D efforts, considers the effects of environmental and safety issues, and assesses the dynamics of international markets and players. <br>
