<A NAME = "E-050" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>E-050 Uninterruptible Power
Supplies:  Continuous Data and Network Service</b></A><BR>
The consequences of interrupted or altered power supply can be severe.  In addition to damaged
equipment which must be replaced, lost data and communications often result in costly delays and
faulty information, translating into lost revenue and customer dissatisfaction.  This BCC study
examines the evolution of  power supply products and software into an industry that can assure
continuity of power to a single desktop computer as well as to complex networks of
telecommunications and information processing systems. The market is segmented by products
that range from battery backups to transmission, switching and operation systems that reroute
signals around a cable break or node outage.  BCC also examines the worldwide factors affecting
the growth of the power supply market.  The current status of products, materials and software is
analyzed and growth trends are predicted.  Profiles of major companies are provided. <br>
Published <b>February 1993</b>  134 pages  
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<A HREF="E050.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "G-067X" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>G-067X Printed Circuit Boards:
Markets & Opportunities</b></A><BR>
Printed circuit board manufacturing is changing as new regulations mandate the use of new
environmentally-compatible materials and processes.  This comprehensive BCC study examines
printed circuit board technology and its impact on PCB fabricators, materials suppliers, and
electronic equipment manufacturers.  Topics addressed include the unification of wafer and PCB
fabrication; advanced materials and processes; imaging technology; fine-line and high-speed
devices; multilayer trends; and environmental issues.  PCB industry structure and players are
examined.  Technology developments and R&D efforts are analyzed.  Detailed market projections
are provided in light of environmental and regulatory developments. <br>
Published <b>September 1994</b>              158 pages                 
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<A HREF="G067X.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "G-070N" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>G-070N Wire, Cable & Fiber
Optics</b></A><BR>
BCC report identifies the wire and cable industry segments that have grown and those that will
grow in an environment affected by fiber optics. It covers the products and materials used for
electronics, building installations and the internal makings of apparatus and it tabulates the present
and likely future needs of the telecommunications, computers, electronics and defense industries
with estimates and forecasts of materials consumption based on analysis of quantitative and
qualitative trends. The study factors into its conclusions the problems and opportunities that
emerge with new technologies, a competitive environment, regulatory issues, and other factors.
Consideration is given to emerging technologies and new materials. Detailed market projections
are provided through 1996.<br>
Published <b>May 1991</b> 131 pages 
Price:  <b>$2450.00</b>
<A HREF="G070N.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "G-089R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>G-089R Advanced Building
Control Systems and Devices:  Products for Intelligent Buildings</b></A><BR>
ABC systems and devices are projected to grow 9% annually topping $283 million by 1995. BCC
report analyzes the market for Advanced Building Communication and Control Devices and
Systems (ABCs) in residential, commercial, industrial and institutional buildings. Safety devices,
HVAC, lighting, CCUs, media, sensors and other system components are discussed in terms of
industry structure, product offerings, technology, services, the major players, and marketing
strategies with forecasts through 1995. This study assesses the impact of all the related trends and
patterns on the future of ABCs. Among these are construction industry outlooks, demographics,
deregulation, declining prices in electronic products, and merger and acquisition activity. <br>
Published <b>May 1990</b> 160 pages 
Price:  <b>$1950.00</b>
<A HREF="G089R.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "G-100R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>G-100R  Smart
Cards</b></A><BR>
This BCC report examines exactly how today's $75.23 million embryonic marketplace will
experience rapid growth in the 1990s, with a comprehensive analysis of the smart card industry,
its structure, market dynamics, technologies, customer bases and timetables for the card's
adoption.  Cost-pricing data and projections are made for 1990, 1995, and 2000 for all major
smart card types and their accompanying readers.  15 separate market segments are identified for
significant smart card penetration.  Opportunities within each market segment are discussed with
concrete quantitative data about the potential card universe of each.  Likely card and reader
populations are forecast for each market segment and financial projections of the dollar volume of
cards and readers are presented. <br> 
Published <b> January 1991</b> 175 pages  
Price:  <b>$2350.00</b>
<A HREF="G100R.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "G-117" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>G-117  Neural Networks,
NeuroComputing & Beyond</b></A><BR>
BCC report evaluates the current R&D, competing technologies, new companies and large
corporations, along with the emerging markets. Assessments are made of the performance claims
for adaptiveness and responsiveness. Technical evaluations and market projections are presented
for such application areas as image and signal processing, decision-making systems, and
knowledge processing. Covers backpropagation, counterpropagation, and other hybrid models.
Considerable attention is also given to the hardware involved. Opportunities are considered for
use in such areas as insurance, finance, defense, medicine and industry. <br>
Published <b>March 1990</b> 346 pages 
Price:  <b>$1950.00</b>
<A HREF="G117.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "G-124" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>G-124  Microsensors Fabrication and
Applications</b></A><BR>
BCC report projects U.S. sales for silicon sensors in all types of applications to grow at an
average annual rate of 10.38% from $763 million in 1989 to $1,376 million in 1995. The in-depth
BCC analysis investigates the current state of micromachine research and technology (at
universities and institutions) to determine its impact in the manufacture of microsensors, quantify
its market potential for the various types of microsensor applications, and identify the companies
most active. The first part of the study defines and describes manufacturing processes. The major
part of the study deals with applications in microsensors. These applications are discussed for the
following industries: medicine, clean room technology, space, integrated microsensor chips, fiber
optics, microbots, microsensors, automobiles, printing devices, aircraft and defense. Within each
industry the various applications are analyzed with information about current manufacturing
activities, products already in the market, volume of output (by value and by quantity), usage and
sales projections through 1995, and the companies involved. <br> 
Published <b>April 1990</b> 151 pages 
Price:  <b>$1850.00</b>
<A HREF="G124.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "G-129" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>G-129  PC LAN Connectivity
Technology</b></A><BR>
BCC report examines the LAN connectivity industry, highlighting the trends that are influencing
the business. The report tabulates the number of installed bases and describes the types of
products in the market. Also discussed are main LAN protocols and their specific functions with
projections for Ethernet, Token-Ring and Novell through 1995. Fiber optics and its influences are
fully assessed. Each product group is examined in terms of types, characteristics, function, and
technological driving forces with projections for market growth. An international perspective is
presented and companies involved are profiled with descriptions of products manufactured and
recent activities.<br>
Published:  <b>May 1991</b>        179 Pages 
Price:  <b>$1950.00</b>
<A HREF="G129.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "G-136" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>G-136 Fiber Optics Technology: 
Applications, Cables & Components</b></A><BR>
The role of fiber optics in modern-day networking is changing as quickly as the technology is
developed.  This extensive BCC analysis covers all relevant aspects of the U.S. fiber optic
media/connectivity marketplace.  Topics covered include industry standards and government
regulations, overall industry structure, market forces influencing demand, and new technological
developments.  Fiber optic cables are examined by product types, detailing general purpose
cables, local area networks, heavy duty applications, telecommunication cables, interbuilding
super trunk cables, and multipurpose cables.  Connectivity products such as laser diode pulses,
connectors, passive couplers, splices, detectors, and optical switches are discussed.  Market
projections are provided by market, product and application. <br>
Published <b>December 1991</b> 147 pages 
Price:  <b>$2350.00</b>
<A HREF="G136.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "G-152" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>G-152  PCMCIA Technology:
Impressive Growth Through 2000, Uncertainty  Beyond</b></A><BR>
After years of being on the edge of success, the PC Card is at last poised to forge its place in the
computing marketplace.  The mobile computer user specifically is benefiting from the convenience
of the card's three small form factors, which offer, primarily, highly portable communication
connectivity and memory expansion.  This BCC report assesses the potential for market growth
through the year 2000 in fax modem, LAN, pager, and multi-function communication cards. 
Furthermore, a detailed comparison of Flash cards versus miniaturized hard disk drive cards is
offered, as well as a look at emerging markets for interface adaptors and other PC Card
applications.  The study also assesses the promise and problems to be faced by the technology
after the turn of the century. <br>
Published: <b>March 1995</b>              149 pages                         
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<A HREF="G152.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "GB-128R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>GB-128R  Thick and Thin Films
in Microelectronics</b></A><BR>
The markets for thick and thin films will increase in value from a total of $839 million in 1992 to
$1.2 billion in 1997 and $1.6 billion by the end of the decade.  This BCC report provides an
in-depth look at thick and thin film technology, applications and materials as they impact the
worldwide electronics industry.  The changing packaging environment is highlighted and the use
of thick films, thin films and combinations for semiconductors and microelectronic components
are analyzed.  The value of thick and thin films is projected by function, type of material, and
application.  Industry structure is presented and profiles of leading material suppliers are included. 
Current market analyses and forecasts through 2000 are provided. <br>
Published: <b>July 1993</b>  
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<A HREF="GB128R.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "GB-138R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>GB-138R  Multichip Packaging
and Bare Chip Systems</b></A><BR>
Global economics are stimulating the multichip module (MCM) market as demand rises for high
performance electronic products. This new BCC report covers the rapidly growing MCM
marketplace. New MCM applications, technologies, and opportunities are discussed and
evaluated. Government initiatives, industry partnerships and consortiums, and other economic
developments affecting the MCM market are detailed. Company activities are examined.
Extensive market projections are provided through the end of the decade. Company profiles are
given, as well as a complete assessment of worldwide market activity in the exciting and evolving
MCM industry. <br>
Published <b>January 1994</b> 257 pages 
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<A HREF="GB138R.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "GB-148" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>GB-148 Electronic Connector
Materials</b></A><BR>
This study identifies the various materials used in the production of electronic connectors and
evaluates their present and future markets.  The materials used in all the different types of
connectors, including rectangular, printed circuit board (PCB), coaxial, cylindrical and other
special type connectors and parts, are discussed in terms of new technology and future
applications.  Materials used for both contacts and connector housings/shells/bodies are included
in the report.  Materials discussed include:  hypalon, silicone, neoprene, ceramics, polyester,
nylon, diallyl phthalate, precious metals, beryllium-copper, copper, tin, nickel and many others.
Specific market projections by size and value are provided through the end of the decade. Major
players participating in this rapidly evolving marketplace are discussed in detail. <br>
Published <b>January 1992</b> 148 pages  
Price: <b>$2350.00</b>
<A HREF="GB148.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "GB-156" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>GB-156 Advanced Electronic
Packaging Systems Technology Through 2000</b></A><BR>
This BCC report describes the technology, processes, materials and performance criteria relating
to state-of-the-art electronics systems. Chip complexity, electronic packaging options for
multichip modules, TAB, chip-on-board and printed circuit interconnections are identified and
quantified. The study identifies new materials being utilized for requirements of higher speeds,
densities and heat, and smaller size. Report analyzes worldwide trends in advanced systems by
type and relationship to electronic industry sectors. Production trends are highlighted, with
industry consumption by material, device, interconnect, and electronic equipment applications
through the year 2000. Activities of materials suppliers, components, and electronic equipment
suppliers are profiled. <br>
Published <b>August 1992</b> 137 pages  
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<A HREF="GB156.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<A NAME = "GB-160" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"><b>GB-160   Magnetic/Opto-Magnetic
Storage: Media and Materials</b></A><BR>
Over the past decade, the concept of "storage" has been revolutionized via the creation of high
capacity magnetic and optical computer media.  Even the definition of stored material has been
considerably broadened to include printed materials, photos, diagrams, and illustrations, among
others.  The advent of improved magnetic and newer optical devices also has made transmission
of information a more viable option.  New storage media will have increasing impact on music and
video industries as well, with the popularity of compact disc technology.  This comprehensive
BCC report covers the products and technologies involved in this changing marketplace, with
specific examination of  downsizing of form, falling prices, and high density developments.  Major
players are profiled, with market projections provided through 1997. <br>
Published <b>September 1992</b> 167 pages   
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<A HREF="GB160.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>


<b><a name = "GB-185" href="bcc_order_report.html">GB-185 Hot Markets: Thermal
Management Technology for Electronics</a></b><br>
The development of increasingly more complex and more highly integrated circuits, with higher
power density, has resulted in the need for improved thermal management in the large variety of
electronic goods in which they are used today.  Heat affects the electrical characteristics, as well
as the chemical and mechanical properties, of the materials and devices that make up electronic
equipment, and excessive heat can result in premature equipment failure.  This BCC report
examines the markets for the various materials, products, and technologies available to the
industry, from substrate materials to active and passive heat sinks using gas, liquid, and two-phase
technologies through 2001.  The document also examines the structure of each industrial segment,
provides a comprehensive patent analysis, and tracks technological developments.<br>
Published <b>January 1996</b>165 pages                 
Price: <b>$2750.00</b>
<A HREF="GB185.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>

<b><a name = "GB-186" href="bcc_order_report.html">GB-186 Thin Layer Depositional
Technologies: Opportunities for the Future</a></b><br>

The ability to deposit thin layers of materials on a variety of substrates has played an important
role in the growth of
several key industries such as microelectronics. A current BCC study indicates that deposition will
expand into the next
century because of the emergence of products that require precise fabrication, and the continued
improvement and
expansion of deposition technologies.  The products include sub-half micron semiconductors,
multiple layer modules,
flat panel displays, an array of wireless equipment, and many other devices that require special
coatings and treatments. 
The expanded deposition techniques include plasma-assisted CVD, ion beam assisted deposition,
spin-coating, and
pulsed laser deposition.<br><p>

In this trilogy of reports, BCC examines these deposition technologies, the materials used and
their properties.  Current
markets are defined, growth factors are analyzed and projections made.  Each process is analyzed
by technology,
materials, and markets.<br><p>


<b>GB-186A Thin Layer Deposition: Highlighting CVD</b> <br>Published <b>July 1996 </b>  157 pages    Price: <b>$2750.00</b><A HREF="GB186A.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>
<p>
<b>GB-186B Thin Layer Deposition: Highlighting PVD</b><br>
Published:<b> September 1996</b>    93 pages  Price:<b> $2750.00</b>
<A HREF="GB186B.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>
<p>
<b>GB-186C Thin Layer Deposition: Plasma Epithaxial</b><br>
Published:<b> November 1996</b>          Price: <b>$2750.00</b><br>
<A HREF="GB186C.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>
<p>
<i>Buy Any Two of the GB-186 series for $3600.00, or All Three for $4100.00</i><p>


<b><a name = "GB-190" href="bcc_order_report.html">GB-190 Waveguide and Waveguide
Materials</a></b><br>
This comprehensive BCC report delves into the markets and technologies for the waveguide
market.  Applications for telecommunications, sensors, medical and dental equipment, process
control instruments, spectrometers, biosensors, gyroscopes, military and the newer potential
applications of optical data storage or optical computing are covered.  Markets are examined and
forecast by product type and applications.  Technologies, international aspects and patents
covered also.  Major companies profiled.<br>
Published: <b> December 1996</b>    278 pages     Price:<b>  $3000.00</b> <A HREF="GB190.html"><I>Show contents</i><p></A>

