<HR><P>
<B><A NAME = "GB-103R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-103R Advanced Optical Materials</b></a><BR>
The markets for advanced optical materials will grow significantly over the next 10 years, but the growth segments of the industry must be selected carefully to capitalize on specific commercial and military needs. BCC report identifies these markets with surgical precision, discussing the emerging commercial and military applications for advanced optical materials used in advanced optics, lasers, mirrors, and detectors from the ultraviolet to the infrared, in terms of market size and growth, technology evaluations, and existing and future applications. Major topics considered include infrared materials, broadband materials, ultraviolet materials, and detector materials. <br>
Published <b>October 1990</b> 235 pages 
Price:  <b>$2950.00</b>
<a href="GB103R.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "G-116R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">G-116R Fiber Optic Sensors</b></a><BR>
Until recently, most fiber optic sensors could be found only at the research level or in advanced military applications.  Now, however, fiber optic sensors are being used in a variety of industrial, aerospace, and military applications.  This new BCC study examines the rapidly evolving market for fiber optic sensors.  Fiber optic sensor technology is detailed, along with advantages and disadvantages.  Types of fiber optic sensors - extrinsic, intrinsic, hybrid - are painstakingly analyzed.  Companies and organizations involved in research, manufacture and sales of fiber optic sensors are profiled.  Extensive market projections are provided through 1998. <br>
Published <b>March 1994</b> 144 pages 
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<a href="G116R.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-141" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-141 Optical Thin-Film Coatings</b></a><BR>
Thin-film coatings are essential for successful performance of almost all optics ranging from simple camera lenses to sophisticated multilayer coatings for sensitive military-related optical  sensors.  Optical coatings are used throughout the optical spectrum from the deep ultraviolet to the far infrared.  The billion-dollar thin-film industry is still alive and doing quite well considering the overall poor state of the advanced optics industry in the U.S.  Though the large majority of optics used are imported, most of the advanced coating is produced domestically.  Furthermore, most of the important advanced optics over the last few years have come from the coatings, rather than from new substrates.  This BCC report provides a thorough worldwide technical-market analysis of the coating materials, equipment, technology, companies, and services during the last decade of the century. <br>
Published <b>April 1991</b> 330 pages 
Price:  <b>$2950.00</b>
<a href="GB141.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-144" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-144 Opportunities for Transferring Defense-Related Advanced Optics Technologies</b></a><BR>
This timely BCC report investigates the potential for transfer of defense-related optics/electro-optics technology to the commercial marketplace.  Issues covered include: What will the markets for defense-related advanced optical applications look like over the next 5 - 10 years?  What commercial applications are most likely to benefit from defense-related optical and electro-optical technology?  What are these markets worth?  Which are the principal companies, government agencies and laboratories, and universities involved?  What are the problems related to transferring defense technology to commercial applications?  How does a company make the transition?<br> 
Published <b>October 1991</b> 280 pages 
Price:  <b>$2950.00</b>
<a href="GB144.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-150" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-150 Optically Active Polymers, Organometallics, and Biomolecular Materials/Devices</b></a><BR>
New polymers for optical and electronic applications are being developed at a rapid pace. These exciting new materials will lead to potentially huge markets for many different applications in the fields of communications, industry, medicine, sensing, and research. Although research on these materials is rapidly advancing, commercial applications are still several years away. Nonetheless, now is the time to be seriously investigating the potential for the new advanced optical and electronic polymers. This new BCC report describes current research, the companies, government agencies, and universities worldwide, that are involved in this work. Potential markets, applications, and market values are identified and characterized. <br>
Published <b>December 1991</b> 186 pages 
Price:  <b>$2250.00</b>
<a href="GB150.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-162" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-162 Advanced Transportation Control Systems: Millimeter Wave, Microwave, and Optical</b></a><BR>
New transportation control systems are slated by many to become the most exciting advance in automotive technology in decades. This comprehensive BCC report explores rapidly advancing automotive control systems which will provide vastly greater safety, ease of operation, and comfort for almost all motor vehicles. Applications for these systems include collision avoidance, night and poor weather vision, "intelligent" cruise control, automatic toll collection, traffic control and auto guidance systems. The study discusses technologies, applications, companies, organizations, academic institutions, and government laboratories which are involved in this research. Report provides detailed market evaluation into the next century. <br>
Published <b>January 1993</b> 238 pages 
Price:  <b>$2450.00</b>
<a href="GB162.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME = "GB-179" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-179 Growing Markets for Laser Materials and Components</b></a><BR>
As the use of lasers in all types of applications continues to grow, so too does the demand for the materials and components that are used in lasers.  A variety of materials and components are being developed that give lasers important new capabilities.  This market research report examines the fast changing market for laser materials and components and tracks the trends shaping this industry.  The main areas covered by this report are components and subassemblies, which range from detectors to modulators; equipment, including amplifiers and power supplies; and materials, which include crystals, dyes, and optical materials.  Components used in diode lasers, including drivers and controllers, are also examined in-depth.  In addition, an analysis is presented for instruments related to the use of lasers, including beam analyzers, pulse and delay generators, optical tables, and positioning equipment.  For each of these areas, detailed market forecasts and market shares are presented, and technology as well as industry trends are analyzed. <br>
Published <b>September 1995</b>                            
Price: <b>$2750.00</b>
<a href="GB179.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>

<b><A NAME = "GB-187" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-187 Future for Optical Coatings</b></a><BR>
The market for optical coatings and services has not been thoroughly analyzed for several years.  The market for optical coatings is highly stratified and competitive and requires extensive analysis to fully understand, provided by this study from BCC.

For the last several years, the optical coating industry has undergone significant change.   The recent changes are creating a market that is in flux for both optical coatings manufacturers and service companies, as well as end users. This BCC report follows new technological developments have made a variety of new coatings materials and deposition processes widely available for the first time.  This study attempts to identify the major industry movements and trends and to serve as a guide for suppliers, manufacturers, and 
users of this technology.<br> 

Published <b>September 1996</b>   138 pages                         
Price: <b>$2950.00</b>
<a href="GB187.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>
 
