<b> <A NAME = "P-123" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"> P-123  Plastics/Elastomers Under the Hood</b> </a><BR>
In the complex and dynamic under-the-hood parts market, BCC estimates consumption of elastomers to remain relatively flat while plastics consumption will grow at an annual rate of 4.7% to reach 732 million lbs. by 1995. This BCC report presents a comprehensive qualitative and quantitative analysis of polymers used in key under-the-hood applications. A review is presented of consumption of elastomers and plastics, as well as special higher-performance materials including silicone, fluoro-resins and elastomers used in gaskets, seals, housings, hose and tubing, wire and cable, belting, engine mounts, connectors and mechanical goods in the passenger car and truck markets. Applications covered are engine, radiator, electrical, transmission, brake, fuel system, power train, steering and the electrical system. The report emphasizes the effect of changing performance criteria on the development and use of new and high-performance materials in these applications. Key suppliers of materials and fabricators of plastic and elastomeric parts are identified, as are the practices of the Big Three U.S. auto companies, as well as those of Japanese and Korean transplants. <br>
