The range of polyethylene and polypropylene polymers, copolymers and alloys/blends is broadening dramatically as the resin manufacturers seek to improve the cost/performance of the olefinics in existing applications and to penetrate some application strongholds of the engineering thermoplastics. Furthermore, the resin manufacturers and the independent compounders are then tailoring plastic material properties further by additive and reactive compounding. This BCC report covers the driving forces, the technologies, the grades and the markets for these new olefinic materials. <br>
