<b> <A NAME = "P-136" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"> P-136 Electroactive Polymers:  New Surge of Interest in the 1990's </b> </a><BR>
As the electrical and electronic equipment industry has grown and diversified, so has the development of new materials that can cost-effectively offer innovative combinations of properties for myriad applications. Polymers are contributing to the advance of electrical/electronic component design, and they offer enormous potential in this field in the years ahead. The key is to either alter the molecular make-up of the polymer or combine it with other organic and inorganic materials to change resistivity levels and other critical electrical properties. The result is the accelerating development of inherently conductive polymers, conductive filled plastics, non-linear optic films and substrates, and a host of other novel polymer-based rigid and flexible materials. Report identifies the various technologies used, the primary players, and the applications open to these materials.<br>
