<b> <A NAME = "P-139" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"> P-139 Environmentally Impacted Additives for Plastics: Winners and Losers</b> </a><BR>
The U.S. plastics resins industry and the additive systems it employs are beset by several environmental issues which will continue to have implications for future demand due to new legislative regulations.  The properties these additives purport are still needed.  This study identifies the additives which are and are not vulnerable to impending regulatory constraints.  Moreover, it identifies and forecasts market trends for replacement additives.  Categories include flame retardants, foaming agents, stabilizers, plasticizers, colorants, compatibilizers, impact modifiers, coupling agents, degradability additives, biocides, polyurethane catalysts, and mold release agents.   In each additive category, all environmentally-related issues are identified, supplier options to deal with the issue are discussed, and the impact on specific chemicals is quantified.  Market projections based upon value and volume are provided. <br>
