<b> <A NAME = "P-142" HREF="bcc_order_report.html"> P-142 The Evolving Market for Caulks & Sealants</b> </a><BR>
Caulks and sealants are rarely given too much attention if they work well.  However, poor performance by a caulk or sealant can destroy the integrity of almost any product.  The market for caulks and sealants bears careful attention as suppliers scramble to reduce VOCs, improve product performance, and identify new opportunities.  Generally, caulks and sealants are used for waterproofing, the prevention of heat loss, soundproofing, cushioning, and window insulation.  This comprehensive BCC study identifies and examines the fundamental raw materials used to manufacture caulks and sealants, such as silicones, butyls, vinyl acetate, acrylics, polyurethanes, epoxies, polysulfides, furan resins, elastomers, PVC, and other resins.  Different product forms such as putty, gunnable, hot-melt, aerated, anaerobic, pre-formed, semi-rigid, intumescent, solvent-based, water-based, and reactive non-volatiles are examined.  Market projections are provided, along with profiles of major companies involved in the caulk and sealant business. <br>
