<TITLE>WASTE MANAGEMENT TECHNOLOGY</TITLE>
<body><IMG SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO"><BR>
<H4>WELCOME TO BCC WASTE MANAGEMENT MARKET REPORTS</H4>
Below you will find a list and summaries of all the reports in our
catalog. If you have any questions about our report, or are
interested in ordering a report, click on the title.<P>
<B>

<a href="#C-002U">Specialty Water Treatment Chemicals</a><BR>
<a href="#C-059R">Technologies for Management of Hazardous Waste</a><BR>
<a href="#C-110R">Bioremediation of Hazardous Wastes, Wastewater,  and Municipal Waste</a><BR>
<a href="#C-166">Catalysts for Environmental Management</a><BR>
<a href="#DWA95">1995 Water Technology Review</a><br>
<a href="#E-049N">Air Pollution and the Market for Monitors and Sensors</a><BR>
<a href="#E-052">Environmental Services for Indoor Air Pollution</a><BR>
<a href="#E-053">Waste-to-Energy:  Impact, Directions and Trends</a><BR>
<a href="#E-056">Building and Industrial Air Filtration</a><BR>
<a href="#E-063">Smoke Stack Cleanup: Technologies, Markets</a><BR>
<a href="#E-064">Air Pollution Control Techniques, Equipment, and Services in Europe</a><BR>
<a href="#E-065">Water Pollution in Europe</a><BR>
<a href="#E-066">Waste Management & Soil Pollution Technology in Europe</a><BR>
<a href="#E-068">Sensors and Monitors for Water Pollution Control</a><BR>
<a href="#E-072">VOC Control Technology: Markets & Applications</a><BR>
<a href="#GB-131R">Conformal Coatings in the Global Electronics Industry</a><BR>
<a href="#GB-140">Consumer Water Treatment Products Highlighting Point-of-Use Water</a><BR>
<a href="#GB-143">Protective Coatings and Linings for Pipes and Tanks</a><BR>
<a href="#GB-147A">Selected Components In Original Equipment Installations</a><BR>
<a href="#GB-147B">Instrumentation for High Purity Water Treatment Systems</a><BR>
<a href="#GB-147C">Consumables for High Purity Water Treatment Systems</a><BR>

</B>
<HR>
<P>
<b><A NAME="C-002U" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-002U  Specialty Water Treatment Chemicals</A></B><BR>
Specialty WTC represents an increasingly critical industry with three major markets:  potable water, process water and wastewater. The next ten years will see a switch from lower-performance, lower-priced commodity WTC to higher-performance, higher-priced specialty WTC. At the same time, related retail market sectors will grow at better than commodity material growth rates. This BCC report is a definitive market study and technical summary for manufacturers, chemical processors, engineers, importers, suppliers and users who work with water treatment chemicals.   Projections are provided  for materials and markets through 2000. <br>
Target Date: <b>September 1995</b>                      
Prepublication Price:  <b>$2150.00</b>
<a href="C002U.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="C-059R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-059R  Technologies for Management of Hazardous Waste</A></B><BR> 
BCC investigates the U.S. market for equipment, chemicals, and services needed in the recycling, disposal, storage, clean-up, neutralization and transportation of organic and inorganic toxic, radioactive, and other hazardous wastes. Study provides historic, current, and predicted sales through 1997, with particular attention given to legislative incentives and disincentives.  The impact of existing and new technologies for filtration separation, recycling, incineration, bio-treatment, chemical neutralization, land filling, underground injection  and others is fully assessed.  Alternatives such as reducing waste generation are explored and the issues of proper disposal and recovery of spilled wastes are addressed. This comprehensive report provides detailed company profiles of the major players active in the hazardous waste field. <br>
Published <b>June 1992</b>  394 pages   Price:  <b>$2550.00</b>
<a href="C059R.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="C-110R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-110R Bioremediation of Hazardous Wastes, Wastewater,  and Municipal Waste</A></B><BR>
This comprehensive BCC technical-economic report evaluates the U.S. markets for microbial environmental management.  Although bioremediation of hazardous wastes are stressed, the scope of the report includes aerobic and anaerobic wastewater and sludge digestion, microbial oil spill remediation, and energy recovery from municipal waste.  Five- and ten-year projections for market activity and value are provided.  Industry structure, associations within the biotechnology industry, pricing trends, R&D, environmental influences, competition with other environmental management technologies and companies are included in this unique market study. <br>
Published <b>April 1993</b> 248 pages 
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<a href="C110R.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="C-166" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">C-166  Catalysts for Environmental Management</A></B><BR>
Much of the environmental management industry's technological base relies on chemical catalysts.  Examples include automotive and plant air pollution abatement, wastewater treatment, and waste minimization catalysts, as well as catalysts used during recycling.  This comprehensive BCC technical-market report evaluates the U.S. markets for environmental management catalysts.  Five- and ten-year market projections are provided for activity and dollar value of catalysts and associated equipment.  Industry structure, price trends, R&D, environmental influences, competition with other environmental management technology are examined in detail. <br>
Published <b>October 1993</b>               202 pages 
Price: <b>$2650.00</b>
<a href="C166.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>

<b> <a name="DWA95" href="bcc_order_report.html">1995 Water Technology Review</a></b><br>
Water purity and water conservation have never been more important, and as a result, water quality rules are becoming more stringent, complex and costly.<p>
The 1995 Water Technology Review is an edited collection of selected papers, highlighting state-of-the-art developments in water technology.  It includes the headline news and the not-so-obvious events having important implications for our business, as well as analysis of sales, prospects, players and applications.<p>
This publication assembles and analyzes the most important development of 1995.  All aspects for the water technology industry are covered, including: the latest news of legislate and regulator activities, key patents, industry developments, instruments and water purifications, recycling processes and ultra pure water treatment.<br>
Published <b>October 1996</b>   302 pages    Price: <b>$1500.00</b>a href="DWA95.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>

<b><A NAME="E-049N" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">E-049N  Air Pollution and the Market for Monitors and Sensors</A></B><BR>
BCC report examines the current status of air pollution and the current monitor/sensor market to identify the significant technological developments, and analyzes trends for the impact they will have on monitor/sensor demand. It assesses the industry structure and the markets for visibility network, remote sensors, ambient, continuous emissions, and point-source monitors by category and type of air pollutant. The amounts of pollutants are quantified by type, and the markets for monitors are analyzed, with estimates of current costs and values along with five-year projections. In-depth company profiles are provided in this unique and timely study. <br>
Published <b>November 1994</b>   191 pages   Price:  <b>$2450.00</b>
<a href="E049N.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="E-052" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">E-052  Environmental Services for Indoor Air Pollution</A></B><BR>
Federal, state and local regulations for various indoor pollutants have created a market for environmental services. This BCC report identifies the settings and markets that hold the greatest promise of future growth and describes the driving forces that are strongest in each-regulatory, economic, health. The study examines services for testing, analyzing and remediating radon, toxic chemicals and airborne pollutants in homes and apartments, office and commercial buildings, factories, plants, and schools. The contaminants of each setting are described for their short and long term real and perceived dangers. Insight is provided into the methods and equipment used to evaluate, remediate and control pollution and how the need to satisfy both health and economic demands are addressed. Equipment, materials and suppliers used are described, and forecasts are made accordingly for market size and sales volume for the next five years. <br>
Published <b>July 1990</b> 150 pages 
Price:  <b>$1950.00</b>
<a href="E052.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="E-053" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">E-053  Waste-to-Energy:  Impact, Directions and Trends</A></B><BR>
BCC estimates that a total of 548 waste-to-energy systems and plants, for all types of waste, will be purchased in 1990.  Growth is forecasted at 2.4% per year to reach an annual expenditure of $1.2 billion by 1995. Tighter federal regulations and environmental controls for waste disposal in landfills have caused many landfills to close while volume of MSM continues to grow. This BCC report makes a thorough assessment of the economics that have led to waste-to-energy plants as an alternative used by municipalities to save tipping fees, and by industries and institutions to save energy costs. The study examines the regulatory environment governing the industry; identifies specific markets for waste and the heat, steam and electricity produced; describes types of systems and equipment required by plants; and points to market leaders of plant operation, the technologies used, and opportunities and pitfalls that prevail.<br>
Published <b>September 1990</b>     155 Pages 
Price:  <b>$1950.00</b>
<a href="E053.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="E-056" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">E-056 Building and Industrial Air Filtration</A></B><BR>
The purity of air in commercial buildings and industrial facilities has always been an important concern for companies from the standpoints of both worker health/safety and productivity.  This unique and comprehensive BCC analysis examines the evolving market for building and industrial air filtration systems in the face of new regulations and air quality standards, various contaminants, and modern factory designs.  Filter media are analyzed by material, application and technology for major industrial sectors. Components, systems, and equipment used in industrial air filtration are discussed, with market projections provided in volume and value terms through 2000.   Major players active in this growing marketplace are profiled and discussed. <br>
Published <b>July 1994</b>     165 pages  
Price: <b>$2450.00</b>
<a href="E056.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="E-063" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">E-063 Smoke Stack Cleanup: Technologies, Markets</A></B><BR>
The new Clean Air Act of 1990 forces industries to clean up air emissions, especially those containing SO2.  Electric utilities, the largest SO2 emitters, can choose from many options to reduce emissions.  When retrofitting power plants, choices range from pre-combustion technologies such as coal cleaning to combustion technologies such as limestone injection and low NOx burners.  Post-combustion technologies such as selective catalytic reduction and sorbent injection also come into play.  A likely, although expensive choice is scrubbers.  This comprehensive BCC study examines these technologies, the economics, the size of the industries, market shares of various emission technologies, scrubber sludge disposal, and other relevant factors. Detailed market projections by application are provided through 2003. Leading companies active in this rapidly evolving marketplace are examined. <br>
Published <b>June 1993</b> 140 pages         
Price: <b>$2450.00</b>
<a href="E063.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="E-064" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">E-064 Air Pollution Control Techniques, Equipment, and Services in Europe</A></B><BR>
Increased public awareness and concern over environmental issues such as acid rain, global warming, and ozone depletion has manifested itself in the Green movement and increased government involvement in environmental protection in Europe. In combination with the continuing economic integration of Western Europe and the emergence of free-market economies in Eastern Europe, this concern will lead to significant business opportunities for suppliers to the $7 billion European market for air pollution control technologies, equipment, and services. This comprehensive BCC report thoroughly analyzes the present and future (1997 and the year 2002) markets for air pollution control equipment for particulate removal and gas treatment, instrumentation and monitoring, and engineering and related environmental services in France, Germany, Italy, the Netherlands, Scandinavia, Spain, the United Kingdom, and other Western Europe and Eastern Europe countries. Particular attention is paid to the prospects for air pollution control equipment such as fabric filters, electrostatic precipitators, wet scrubbing systems, mechanical collectors, flue gas desulphurization (FGD) systems, oxidation systems, and gas absorption & scrubbing systems. <br>
Published <b>December 1992</b> 115 pages 
Price:  <b>$1500.00</b>
<a href="E064.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="E-065" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">E-065  Water Pollution in Europe</A></B><BR>
Water pollution has arisen as an important environmental concern in Europe.  In combination with the drive toward economic integration of Western Europe and the emergence of free-market economies in Eastern Europe, this concern has facilitated the emergence of a multi-billion dollar market for water pollution control technologies in Europe.  This unique and timely BCC study focuses on water treatment equipment, instrumentation and monitoring, and engineering and related environmental services in Europe, a market valued at $7.9 billion in 1992.  Advanced water treatment techniques are also covered in detail.  Market projections are provided through 2002, along with extensive company profiles. <br>
Published <b>January 1993</b> 116 pages  
Price: <b>$1500.00</b>
<a href="E065.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="E-066" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">E-066 Waste Management & Soil Pollution Technology in Europe</A></B><BR>
Like air and water pollution, soil pollution in Europe has attracted a great deal of attention in the past few years, and is expected to continue as a major area of concern and expense. With estimates of the potential market size approaching $30.4 billion, the soil pollution control industry in Europe warrants particularly close consideration. This unique and comprehensive BCC study includes thorough coverage of the underlying social, political and economic issues influencing the soil pollution and control business. Recycling efforts are assessed, as well as new technologies, services and products available. Market projections are provided, along with detailed profiles of companies active in the changing European soil pollution industry. <br>
Published <b>March 1993</b> 135 pages  
Price:  <b>$1500.00</b>
<a href="E066.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="E-068" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">E-068  Sensors and Monitors for Water Pollution Control</A></B><BR>
Sensors and monitors needed for water pollution control and water quality testing are experiencing rising demand.  The increasingly stringent environmental regulations for water quality that are expected to be introduced in the coming years will also stimulate demand for sensors, monitors and related instrumentation.  This innovative BCC report investigates the problems and opportunities for these unique devices in the industrial, commercial, residential and municipal markets.  The full range of pH electrodes, meters and controllers, as well as conductivity meters, nitrate meters, oxygen analyzers, and wastewater/groundwater samplers are examined.  Profiles of major corporate players are provided, along with market projections for this evolving marketplace. <br>
Published <b>August 1993</b> 279 pages  
Price: <b>$2450.00</b>
<a href="E068.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="E-072" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">E-072  VOC Control Technology: Markets & Applications</A></B><BR>
The reduction of volatile organic compound (VOC) emissions has been the subject of seemingly endless debate for many years.  The Clean Air Act Amendments of 1990 tightened restrictions on the output and production of VOCs in the U.S., although implementation of many of the provisions is only now beginning to occur.  This timely BCC report covers the unique problems presented by VOCs, such as atmospheric pollution, acid rain, ozone depletion, and global warming.  Emissions covered include sulfur dioxide, nitrous oxide, carbon dioxide, carbon monoxide, lead, and other gases.  Technologies, systems and equipment used to reduce or eliminate VOCs are detailed, such as catalytic oxidation, thermal oxidation, incineration, adsorption, scrubbing, particulate removal, storage tanks, and new technologies.  Market projections are provided through the end of the decade. <br>
Published <b>October 1994</b>                181 pages                 
Price: <b>$2750.00</b>
<a href="E072.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="GB-131R" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-131R Conformal Coatings in the Global Electronics Industry</A></B><BR>
BCC report describes the technologies, processing methods, and performance criteria for conformal coatings used in all major electronic markets-telecommunications, defense, computers, industrial controls, automotive, instrumentation, consumer electronics, and electronic components. Regulations, specifications, standards and safety considerations are discussed as they apply to the needs of the various end-users. The industry structure is analyzed, and coating suppliers are profiled, with detailed information on their market share (in percent and value), pricing strategies, distribution channels, and packaging. Five- and ten-year market forecasts are provided by industry sector, chemical technology, materials, process technology, and major suppliers. <br> 
Published <b>April 1994</b>  156 pages
Price:  <b>$2750.00</b>
<a href="GB131R.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p> 


<b><A NAME="GB-140" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-140  Consumer Water Treatment Products Highlighting Point-of-Use Water</A></B><BR>
The growth in the demand for consumer point-of-use water improvement products is based primarily on the general increase in water pollution problems, which are present in both well water and urban water systems.  Consumers cope with these problems by treating water.  Treatments and markets analyzed in this BCC report are chemicals such as activated charcoal, various types of filters and membranes, including reverse osmosis, distillation and softening.  Markets include residents, institutions, business and portable.  Also includes bottled drinking water manufacturing.  The report profiles leading manufacturers of these products, including their market shares; examines R&D and relevant patents; and discusses how the products are marketed. <br>
Published <b>March 1992</b>         
Price:  <b>$1950.00</b>
<a href="GB140.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="GB-143" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-143  Protective Coatings and Linings for Pipes and Tanks</A></B><BR>
This BCC report makes a thorough investigation of the markets for pipe and tank coatings and liners used for corrosion resistance, hostile environments, high temperatures, wear and abrasion, electrical insulation, dry lubrications, and non-stick applications.  Markets are identified and segmented by major chemical types.  Major user industries covered include gas, oil, chemical, pulp and paper, pharmaceutical, food, marine, and others.  For each,  markets are analyzed by materials and applications with estimates and forecasts presented in terms of consumption and value.  Comparisons of major technologies and technological trends are made.  The industry structure is described, identifying the suppliers, users, associations, governing bodies and the nature of their activities. <br>
Published <b>September 1991</b>                         177 pages  
Price:  <b>$2750.00</b>
<a href="GB143.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="GB-147A" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-147A Selected Components In Original Equipment Installations</A></B><BR>
Water treatment technologies are expected to exhibit strong growth through the end of the decade.  This unique BCC report, part of the trilogy covering high purity water treatment systems, explores the components/subsystems used in the manufacture or installation of high purity water treatment systems.  Components covered in detail include UV stabilizers, chemical metering pumps, DI water heaters, ozonation equipment, RO pumps and pressure vessels, pressure tanks, and high purity piping systems.  Market size and value projections are provided for each industry segment through 1995. <br>
Published <b>December 1992</b>                            100 pages   
Price: <b>$1550.00</b>
<a href="GB147A.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="GB-147B" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-147B Instrumentation for High Purity Water Treatment Systems</A></B><BR>
Instrumentation plays a critical role in the proper functioning of high purity water treatment systems, and has become, in effect, a marketplace unto itself.  The second in the BCC water treatment trilogy, this market analysis focuses the instrumentation for high purity water treatment systems, which has become a multi-million dollar subindustry.  Covered in this study are TOC analyzers, liquid particle counters, silica analyzers, data logging systems, pH measurement devices, sodium analyzers, ion chromatography devices, and conductivity and resistivity instrumentation.  Growth in terms of market size and value is predicted for all categories through 1995. <br>
Published <b>April 1992</b>                                
Price: <b>$1250.00</b>
<a href="GB147B.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>


<b><A NAME="GB-147C" HREF="bcc_order_report.html">GB-147C  Consumables for High Purity Water Treatment Systems</A></B><BR>
Consumables represent an exceedingly important segment of the market for high purity water treatment systems.  The third report in the water treatment trilogy, this study analyzes consumables for high purity water treatment systems.  Cartridge filters, ion exchange resins, RO cleaning chemicals, RO membranes, and RO scale inhibitors, among others.  Projections are provided in terms of market size and value through 1995. <br>
Published <b>April 1992</b>                                
Price: <b>$1250.00</b>
<a href="GB147C.html"><I>Show contents</i></a><p>



