<H3 ALIGN=center>NEW INGREDIENTS AND PROCESSES

ARE REVOLUTIONIZING THE FOOD INDUSTRY</H3>

<BODY>

As you well know, new food ingredients and processes are figuring more and

more 

prominently in the production of more nutritious and better balanced designer

foods. 

At the same time, some developments such as those from biotechnology are being 

opposed by consumer groups. The dizzying pace of industry announcements and 

shifting tastes can confound even the most alert formulator.  

</BODY>

<H4 ALIGN=center>THAT'S WHY YOU SHOULD BE READING

FOOD INGREDIENT NEWS</H4>

<BODY>

Marketers, processors, R&D managers, planners, and food engineers and chemists 

agree that <B>FOOD INGREDIENT NEWS</B> is an indispensable resource. With its 

comprehensive coverage of new products, <B>FOOD INGREDIENT NEWS</B> provides one-

stop shopping for the news of new flavors and enhancers, healthy light and

clean 

label products, fortifiers and nutraceuticals, as well as functional

additives and basic 

ingredients. 

<P>

In addition, <B>FOOD INGREDIENT NEWS</B> reports on important clinical studies and 

research that can cause dramatic shifts in public taste and eating habits;

tracks the 

prices of important raw materials; and follows the activities of regulatory

agencies. 

Items contain the name, address and phone number of contacts so it's easy to

act on 

new information. 

<P>

Long before the news appears in the industry trade press, subscribers to <B>FOOD 

INGREDIENT NEWS</B> are informed of:



<UL><LI>    New products and new technologies in ingredients and ingredient development

<LI>    Research studies that suggest benefits or harmful effects from certain ingredients

<LI>    Industry news, capacity, supply and demand

<LI>    Company news, who is expanding, mergers and acquisitions, new business units and reorganizations

<LI>    New regulations, and labeling rules.</UL>



Become a regular reader of <B>FOOD INGREDIENT NEWS</B>. <BR>Just fill in the <A HREF="bcc_order_news.html"><I>order

form</I></A> and you will receive 12 issues for only $325.

