<H3 ALIGN=center>The Implications of the Revolution in Stereochemistry 

May Be More Profound Than Biotechnology</H3>

<BODY>

A  hidden but surging new industry is transforming the chemical, pharmaceutical, 

and biotechnology industries. Chiral, cis/trans positional and other isomers of 

organic compounds will have enormous economic impact. <BR>

<P>

Chemists have long known since the time of Pasteur that the same molecule can take more than 

one shape. And they have long been aware that these enantiomers of the same chemical can 

vary significantly in activity. But only recently have they learned to synthesize pure forms of 

optically active isomers. This technology has now become one of the hottest areas of chemical 

research. Key patents are flowing from the labs; sales of new products are growing in excess of 

10% a year and are rapidly approaching the billion dollar mark.<BR> 

<P>

Analysts are not just making blue sky predictions. The promise of stereochemistry is very real

and it is being realized. More effective drugs, higher specificity pesticides, purer colors and dyes, 

intense flavors and aromas are already being produced. Biochemicals, petrochemicals, 

surfactants, liquid crystals, binary optical materials, and even surface coatings are benefiting. 

Suppliers, from instrument and reagent producers, to manufacturers and developers of 

membranes and other separation technology are also poised for profits. 

</BODY>

<H4 ALIGN=center>That's Why You Should Be Reading

Stereochemical Technology News</H4>

<BODY>

<B>Stereochemical Technology News</B> is a new newsletter that will keep you informed of key 

developments. Each month, <B>Stereochemical Technology News</B> will report on:

<UL><LI>

<LI>         Stereoselective Synthesis	

<LI>	 Markets and Trends

<LI>	 Analysis of Isomeric Compounds

<LI>	 Catalysts and Transformation Agents 

<LI>	 Separation Technology			

<LI>	 New Applications

<LI>	 Raw Materials and Intermediates		

<LI>	 Reaction Strategies		

<LI>	 Patents and Research Reports		

<LI>	 Industry News</UL>



Each issue of <B>Stereochemical Technology News</B> will keep you up to date in this fast changing 

technology.  Key licenses and technology transfer offerings are featured; supply and demand for 

new materials, products and processes are covered; new instruments and separation technology 

are described. Items contain the name, address and phone number of contacts so it's easy to act 

on new information. <BR>

<P>

Become a regular reader of <B>Stereochemical Technology News</B>. <BR>Just fill in the <A HREF="bcc_order_news.html"><I>order form</I></A> and you will receive 12 issues for only $375.

