<H3 ALIGN=center>AS BIOTECHNOLOGY MATURES, KEEPING ABREAST OF

DEVELOPMENTS IS MORE IMPORTANT THAN EVER! </H3>

<BODY>

Gee-whiz breakthroughs aren't splashed across the front pages so often these

days. But that 

doesn't mean nothing is going on. To the contrary, the developments occurring

now are the ones 

that really matter. Biotechnology is making  good on its promise to transform

a broad range of 

industries and technologies. </BODY>

<H4 ALIGN=center>That's why Applied Genetics News is essential reading.</H4> 

<BODY>

Now in its 15th year, <B>Applied Genetics News</B>  has charted the evolution of

biotechnology from 

the beginning. Today, its unique blend of technology and economics coverage

provides  key 

insights not found in the general press.

<P>

Corporate executives, scientists, and industry observers worldwide rely on 

<B>Applied Genetics 

News</B> to stay up-to-date on the latest developments in research, manufacturing,

marketing and 

investing. <B>Applied Genetics News</B> provides concise timely  reporting and

analysis that will help 

you keep up with what's going on and keep you ahead of your competition.

<P>

Every month, <B>Applied Genetics News</B> reports on new products, new technologies

and new 

applications. It follows the corporate giants and the startups, the venture

capital and the stock 

offerings.  And it covers the issues and the regulators. Each issue also

includes summaries of 

recent patents, licensing agreements, key publications, and schedules of

important meetings. And it 

draws on BCCs business and marketing analysts to place developments in

context. 

<P>

Whatever your industry, whatever your interest, turn to <B>Applied Genetics News</B>

for 

comprehensive coverage of biotechnology:



<UL><LI>  Medicine: Diagnostics, Infectious diseases, Immunotherapy, Neurobiology, Gene therapy.

<LI>  Agriculture: Crop improvement, Livestock breeding, Fats and oils, Food additives and ingredients.

<LI> Environment: Remediation, Waste treatment.

<LI> Chemicals, Enzymes, Bioprocessing Technology

<LI> Technology Transfer 

<LI> Research 

<LI> Strategic Alliances</UL>



Become a regular reader of <B>Applied Genetics News</B>. <BR>Just fill in the <A HREF="bcc_order_news.html"><I>order

form</I></A> and you will receive 12 issues for only $375.

