<H3 ALIGN=center>Where Designer Materials 
Save Lives And Cut Costs</H3>

<BODY>

Nowhere is the ability to tailor the properties of materials having greater impact than in 

the $42 billion medical devices market. Advanced coating technology, new knowledge of 

biocompatibility, and the ability to produce designer materials are creating a broad variety 

of important new medical innovations. New materials for implants, adhesives, imaging 

agents, and drug delivery systems are moving rapidly out of the laboratory and into the 

hospital and clinic.</BODY> 



<H4 ALIGN=center>That's Why You Should Be Reading

Medical Materials Update</H4>

<BODY>

<B>MEDICAL MATERIALS UPDATE</B> will keep you informed of key developments 

affecting the 11,000 companies in the U.S. that rely on high-technology materials to 

develop economical new treatments and devices. Each month, <B>Medical Materials 

Update</B> brings you the latest developments in:

<UL><LI>

<LI>	 Plastics and Polymers

<LI>	 Metals, Ceramics, and Composites

<LI>	 Surface Modifications			

<LI>	 Biologicals and Biomaterials

<LI>	 Gels and Membranes			

<LI>	 New Devices and Applications</UL>



<B>MEDICAL MATERIALS UPDATE</B> will also keep you informed of legislative and 

regulatory activities as the nation devises a new healthcare system. Key patents, licenses 

and technology transfer offerings are featured; supply and demand for new materials, 

products and processes are covered. Items contain the name, address and phone number 

of contacts so it's easy to act on new information. 

<P>

Become a regular reader of  <B>MEDICAL MATERIALS UPDATE</B>. <BR>Just fill in the <A HREF="bcc_order_news.html"><I>order form</I></A> and you will receive 12 issues for only $350.

