<H3 ALIGN=center>THERE ARE NEW ECONOMICS

IN THE OIL PATCH</H3>

<BODY>

It used to be that the cheapest way to maintain supplies of petroleum and

natural 

gas was to continually explore for new reservoirs.  As production from older

wells 

tapered off, they were abandoned and new ones were brought into production.

<P>

Not any more. A combination of advanced technology and environmental 

constraints has made it more economical to keep old wells productive for as

long 

as possible. Indeed, shutting down a well is often more expensive than keeping

it 

producing. New technology also has made it profitable to exploit heavy oils

and 

tar sands that were once considered prohibitively expensive to process and 

refine. 

</BODY>

<H4 ALIGN=center>That's Why You Should Be Reading

 ENHANCED ENERGY RECOVERY NEWS</H4>

<BODY>

Your annual subscription to <B>ENHANCED ENERGY RECOVERY NEWS</B> will keep 

you up to date on this exciting new energy industry. These days, drillers are 

cleaning up well fluids and reusing them rather than having to dispose of

waste; 

they are using drilling techniques that allow them to pinpoint productive 

reservoirs; and they have a bag of new tricks for getting that oil out of the 

ground.  

<P>

Each issue of <B>ENHANCED ENERGY RECOVERY NEWS</B> will keep you informed 

of: 

<UL><LI>

<LI>         MICROBIAL EOR

     HEAVY OIL, TAR SANDS

<LI>         THERMAL RECOVERY

<LI>        CHEMICAL EOR

         MISCIBLE FLOODING

<LI>       ADVANCED REFINING

<LI>         HORIZONTAL DRILLING

<LI>     GAS FLOODING

<LI>         ENVIRONMENT RULES

<LI>       MODELING

<LI>         NEW TECHNOLOGY

<LI>     INTERNATIONAL 

NEWS

</UL>

An annual subscription to <B>ENHANCED ENERGY RECOVERY NEWS</B> will bring 

you also the latest news of legislative and regulatory activities, key

patents, 

industry developments, licenses and technology transfer offerings. Items

contain 

the name, address and phone number of contacts so it's easy to act on new 

information. 

<P>

Become a regular reader of <B>ENHANCED ENERGY RECOVERY NEWS</B>. <BR>Just
fill in the

<A HREF="bcc_order_news.html"><I>order form</I></A> and you will receive 12 issues for only $350.



