<H3 ALIGN=center>Can You Imagine a World Without Batteries?</H3>

<BODY>

Batteries seem quite mundane but think about it for a minute. When you power

up your laptop 

computer, use a portable power tool, look at your wrist watch, brush your

teeth with an electric 

toothbrush, follow lighted signs to emergency exits during power outages,

start your car or listen to 

a favorite CD, you are depending on a battery.  

<P>

Not surprisingly, battery technology is one of the most significant growth

areas of the 1990s. From 

giant utility load leveling batteries to the cells that power heart

pacemakers, developments are 

making batteries one of the most exciting technologies for investors.  

<P>

And this charged up research and development is driving new industries.  In

recent months, for 

example, electric vehicles have demonstrated that they can meet the range and

performance 

requirements of many applications. Indeed, an increasing number of experts

believe that in a few 

years, advanced designs could compete with the family car.  And in a myriad of

uses, from delivery 

vans to commuter cars, urban buses to utility vehicles, they are practical.

Now.

</BODY>

<H4 ALIGN=center>That's Why You Should Be Reading

Battery & EV Technology News</H4>

<BODY>

<B>BATTERY & EV TECHNOLOGY</B> is the only newsletter that covers the full range of

this rapidly 

evolving technology from the tiny cells that power watches to giant batteries

for utility load 

leveling. <B>BATTERY & EV TECHNOLOGY</B> keeps battery makers and users, electric

vehicle 

developers, and industry watchers current on trends in materials, technology,

systems, and 

concepts. Each monthly issue will bring you reports of technical developments,

pressing 

environmental issues, descriptions of important patents, news of technical

conferences and 

meetings, and much more. Items contain the name, address and phone number of

contacts so it's 

easy to act on new information. 

<P>

Your subscription to <B>BATTERY & EV TECHNOLOGY</B> will keep you informed of: 



<UL><LI>  Primary and secondary battery technology

<LI>    Fuel cells

<LI>    Markets and

industry news  

<LI>  Advanced batteries

<LI>    Load leveling batteries

<LI>    Government and industry

R&D  

<LI>  The EV market

<LI>    Recent patents

<LI>    Environmental issues

<LI>    Foreign competition  

<LI>  Emerging markets

<LI>    Chargers and monitoring ....and much, much more. </UL>



Become a regular reader of <B>BATTERY & EV TECHNOLOGY</B>. <BR>Just fill in the <A HREF="bcc_order_news.html"><I>order

form</I></A> and you will receive 12 issues for only $395.

