<HTML>

<H3 ALIGN=center>MATERIALS DEVELOPMENTS DRIVE 

ELECTRONICS TECHNOLOGY</H3>

<BODY>

Nowhere is the new ability to produce "designer materials" more crucial than

in the 

electronics industry. Indeed, semiconductor manufacturers pioneered many of

the 

materials and processes that are now having an important impact in other

industries. 

New materials, from superconducting ceramics to diamond films, will shape the 

electronics industry in the coming decade. Advanced processing technology,

from 

molecular beam epitaxy to nanophase powders, will become increasingly

important.

</BODY>

<H4 ALIGN=center>That's Why You Should Be Reading

Electronic Materials Technology News</H4>

<BODY>

Each monthly issue of <B>ELECTRONIC MATERIALS TECHNOLOGY NEWS</B>  will 

keep you informed on who's involved, what technologies are being developed and 

commercialized, where the growing fields are, which events are likely to shape

the 

trends in the industry and why. Manufacturers, materials suppliers and end

users 

will all benefit from late-breaking news in the rapidly evolving electronic

materials 

industry.

<P>

