<H3 ALIGN=center>New Technology to Produce Designer Materials 

Is Revolutionizing Many Industries</H3>

<BODY>

Not so long ago, surface modification meant little more than coatings that protected from 

corrosion and wear, and thin films were either packaging materials or an esoteric subject for 

physicists. But not any more: a host of new technologies now enable engineers to manipulate 

the properties of materials almost a molecule at a time. Virtually any physical or chemical 

property can be optimized to fit the application.  Products  from machine tools to catalysts 

and semiconductors are being given a competitive edge.<BR> 

<P>

Today, patents are flooding out of the laboratories as developers vie for position in new  thin film 

technology.  Venture capitalists are backing startups in diamond films and superconductors.  And 

established companies in a variety of  industries are making strategic moves to maintain their 

positions.<BR><P>

</BODY>

<H4 ALIGN=center>That's Why You Should Be Reading

 THIN FILM/DIAMOND TECHNOLOGY NEWS</H4>

<BODY>

<B>THIN FILM/DIAMOND TECHNOLOGY NEWS</B> cuts across all industries and scientific 

disciplines to report on the important developments that can improve your products. You 

receive the latest information on surface treatment, from changes in traditional coating 

processes to improvements in the more sophisticated technologies and the use of thin films.

<P>

Each monthly issue of <B>THIN FILM/DIAMOND TECHNOLOGY NEWS</B> will keep you up to 

date on the rapidly evolving thin film processes, from molecular beam epitaxy to the chemical 

vapor deposition technologies that are turning diamond and diamond-like films into an 

important growth industry. 

<P>

An annual subscription to <B>THIN FILM/DIAMOND TECHNOLOGY NEWS</B> will  bring you the 

latest news of:



<B><UL><LI>		Abrasion and Wear Resistance

<LI>		Processing Technology

<LI>		New Equipment

<LI>		Interfaces

<LI>		Electronics

<LI>		Optics

<LI>		Micromachining/Nanotechnology

<LI>		Industry News

<LI>		Testing and Analysis

<LI>		Technology Transfer</UL></B>



Also included is the latest news of legislative and regulatory activities, key patents, industry 

developments, licenses and technology transfer offerings. Items contain the name, address and 

phone number of contacts so its easy to act on new information.<BR> 

<P>

