<H3 ALIGN=center>Regulations, public concern, and increased  industrial 

commitment to a clean environment have created 

a multi-billion dollar business in waste treatment.</H3>

<BODY>

The imperative is simple: produce less waste; clean up the messes of the past. But that 

economic driving force has sparked a growing market for innovative solutions to waste 

handling. Increasingly, technological advances are responding to the demand.<BR>

<P>

The proliferation of advanced treatment methods, products and processes adds up to new opportunities as 

well as new challenges for you and your company.<BR>

<P>

<H4 ALIGN=center>Waste Treatment Technology News 

will help you stake your claim to a share of the profits.</H4> 



<B>WASTE TREATMENT TECHNOLOGY NEWS</B> is a monthly newsletter for business 

and technology executives who need to keep abreast of the rapid technological 

changes that characterize this industry. From acid rain to solid waste, sludge to 

wastewater, medical waste and mine spoils, industrial process water and incinerator 

ash, each issue of <B>WASTE TREATMENT TECHNOLOGY NEWS</B> brings its readers 

