<H3 ALIGN=center>The Impact of Advanced Membranes Now Extends 

from Food and Drug Production to Water Purification

and Semiconductor Manufacturing</H3>

<BODY> 

For years membranes existed as products in search of  the right markets.  Now 

the markets are here, ranging from water purification, ultrapure chemicals, gas 

separations and electrochemistry, to biotechnology, food and cosmetics. 

Membranes and separations have become a multimillion-dollar industry, growing 

at the rate of 10 - 20% per year.  Enthusiasm for membrane applications and 

research abounds with prospects for continued profitability for producers and 

users alike.  

</BODY>

<H4 ALIGN=center>That's Why You Should Be Reading

Membrane & Separation Technology News</H4>

<BODY>

You can rely on <B>Membrane & Separation Technology News</B> to keep you up to 

date about developments in this vigorous and growing technology. Since 1982, 

<B>Membrane & Separation Technology News</B> has provided its readers with  the 

latest news in membrane technology and business. Each issue explores, 

analyzes and reports on the  science, technology and business of :



<UL><LI>	 Microfiltration

<LI>	 Reverse Osmosis 

<LI>	 Ultrafiltration

<LI>	 Pervaporation

<LI>	 Gas Separation

<LI>	 Electrodialysis</UL>



Commercial applications in pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, electronics, water, 

foods, beverages, and pollution control are explored in light of membrane 

technologys cost-effective, energy-efficient properties.  

<P>

An annual subscription to <B>Membrane & Separation Technology News</B> will bring 

you the latest news of legislative and regulatory activities, key patents, industry 

developments, licenses and technology transfer offerings. Items contain the 

name, address and phone number of contacts so its easy to act on new 

information. 

<P>

Become a regular reader of <B>Membrane & Separation Technology News</B>.  <BR>

Just fill in the <A HREF="bcc_order_news.html"><I>order form</I></A> and you will recieve 12 issues for $395.

