<H3 ALIGN=center>Those Who Make the Real Profits are

Those Who Spot Trends First

<BR>

GAIN A PROFITABLE PERSPECTIVE ON CHANGE. 

<BR>SUBSCRIBE TO INDUSTRIES IN TRANSITION</H3>



<BODY>

Whether you are a private investor or a strategic planner, you know that the

investors and companies who 

make a killing are those that spot the trends before everyone else.  Sure,

there are all those stock reports 

and industry gurus but they usually tout old news. 

<P>

We'd like to introduce you to a unique newsletter that will help you identify

the key changes that spell 

profits before your competition. It is called <B>Industries in Transition</B>. 

Unlike most investment newsletter 

we don't track the market, we watch the technology that underlies it. 

</BODY>

<H4 ALIGN=center>Industries in Transition spots the technology 

that will shape tomorrow's markets. </H4>

<BODY>

Each issue of <B>Industries in Transition</B> draws on the expertise of Business

Communications Co.'s team of 

technical marketing analysts. Every year, BCC analysts produce hundreds of

technology/marketing reports 

that sell for thousands of dollars; BCC analysts also produce more than twenty

specialized newsletters that 

track technologies from optics to membranes, electronic to biotechnology.  

<P>

Now you can take advantage of that expertise in an easy to read, monthly

newsletter.  When our analysts 

spot trends that may be included in major studies, they quickly inform the

editors of <B>Industries in 

Transition</B>. These analysts are constantly alert for key developments in

hundreds of industry categories, 

such as advanced transportation, energy, biotechnology, chemicals and

materials, and much more. Each 

month they collect key marketing and technical trends from of a multitude of

sources, both in the U.S. and 

abroad.  

<P>

Our editors cram <B>Indutries in Transition</B> with timely, no-nonsense data in a

form you can use. Illustrated 

with numerous charts and tables, <B>Industries in Transition</B> pinpoints technology

just emerging from the 

labs, targets key technology-driven shifts in industry sectors, and tracks the

major players.

<P>

Whether it's the prospects for CFC replacements or foreign opportunities in

telecommunications or 

supercomputers, growth of carbon fibers or fish farming, <B>Industries in

Transition</B> will give you the 

picture. From fat-free foods to fuel cells,  <B>Industries in Transition</B> spots

the shifts that are key to business 

and investment intelligence. 

<P>

Any item in  <B>Industries in Transition</B> could be the grist for a marketing study

costing several thousand 

dollars, and many are. But with today's tight corporate budgets, few  managers

or investors can purchase 

studies that are not critically important. Instead, they read <B>Industries in

Transition</B>.

<P>

We know you don't have the time in your busy schedule to wade through

thousands of pages of data. Rely 

on <B>Industries in Transition</B> to do the job for you. <B>Industries in Transition</B>

will give you the information 

you need to make strategic decisions.  

<P>

