<H2 ALIGN=center>Forget About Daddy's Buick!</H2>
<BODY>
<P ALIGN=center><B>A revolution in transportation technology is well underway. 
It will have an effect every bit as significant as the invention 
of the steamship, the transcontinental railroad,  
the Ford Model T or the Wright Brothers' airplane.</B> </P>

The prowess of U.S. industry rests on advances in shipbuilding, railroads,
highways, and aircraft.  
Now transportation is being reinvented.  The revolution in smart
transportation systems  will be 
a multi-billion dollar, international industry. Advanced transportation
technologies are being 
investigated for all modes of transportation.  Innovations range from
high-tech sensors to satellite 
communications systems. 
<P>
International funding for IVHS (intelligent vehicle highway systems) is at
unprecedented levels.  
Turnpike authorities and urban transit agencies are testing automated toll
collection systems, 
carmakers are incorporating the first advanced navigation systems as well and
improved control 
and safety devices, new and improved air traffic control systems are being
developed.  
<P>
These programs will create a new industry that could be worth over a billion
dollars in the next 
five years, and many billions of dollars over the next decade. Among the
beneficiaries will be 
sensor manufacturers, communications companies, semiconductor producers, to
name just a 
few. Moreover, it is a great application for technology transfer.</BODY>

<H4 ALIGN=center>ADVANCED TRANSPORTATION TECHNOLOGY NEWS WILL 
KEEP YOU INFORMED OF ALL THE DEVELOPMENTS</H4>
<BODY>
<B>Advanced Transportation Technology News</B> will bring you the latest technical
and business-
related developments in the entire transportation sector.  Not just IVHS, but
the application of 
related technology to rail, ships, and aircraft as well.  Each issue will
report on:

<UL><LI>      Improved Safety Systems Technology
<LI>      Sensors and New Sensor 
<LI>      New Navigation Technology
<LI>      Information/Data Systems
<LI>      Automatic Toll-Collection
<LI>      Maglev and Other New Rail Technologies  
<LI>      Traffic Fleet Management
<LI>      Air/Sea Traffic Control
<LI>      Electronic Funds Transfer
<LI>      Engine Control Technologies</UL>

<B>Advanced Transportation Technology News</B> will keep you up to date on news and
analysis on 
new technology,  funding, joint ventures and other agreements.  It will track
key contracts, from 
bid to award. And it will analyze business decisions, technology, and
competition. 
<P>
Become a regular reader of <B>Advanced Transportation Technology News</B>. <BR>Just fill
in the <A HREF="bcc_order_news.html"><I>order form</I></A> and you will receive 12 issues for only $365.
